47        code. But that info is not passed to emit_S390Instr. Only mode64 is
48        being passed. So, ideally, we want this passed as an argument, too.
49        Until then, we use a global variable. This variable is set as a side
50        effect of iselSB_S390. This is safe because instructions are selected
51        before they are emitted. */

58     /* Decompile the given register into a static buffer and return it */
59     const HChar *
60     s390_hreg_as_string(HReg reg)
61     {
62        static HChar buf[10];
63     
64        static const HChar ireg_names[16][5] = {
65           "%r0",  "%r1",  "%r2",  "%r3",  "%r4",  "%r5",  "%r6",  "%r7",
66           "%r8",  "%r9",  "%r10", "%r11", "%r12", "%r13", "%r14", "%r15"
67        };
68     
69        static const HChar freg_names[16][5] = {
70           "%f0",  "%f1",  "%f2",  "%f3",  "%f4",  "%f5",  "%f6",  "%f7",
71           "%f8",  "%f9",  "%f10", "%f11", "%f12", "%f13", "%f14", "%f15"
72        };
73     
74        UInt r;  /* hregNumber() returns an UInt */
75     
76        r = hregNumber(reg);
77     
78        /* Be generic for all virtual regs. */
79        if (hregIsVirtual(reg)) {
80           buf[0] = '\0';
81           switch (hregClass(reg)) {
82           case HRcInt64: vex_sprintf(buf, "%%vR%d", r); break;
83           case HRcFlt64: vex_sprintf(buf, "%%vF%d", r); break;
84           default:       goto fail;
85           }
86           return buf;
87        }
88     
89        /* But specific for real regs. */
90        vassert(r < 16);
91     
92        switch (hregClass(reg)) {
93        case HRcInt64: return ireg_names[r];
94        case HRcFlt64: return freg_names[r];
95        default:       goto fail;
96        }
97     
98      fail: vpanic("s390_hreg_as_string");
99     }
100     
101     
102     /* Tell the register allocator which registers can be allocated. */
103     void
104     s390_hreg_get_allocable(Int *nregs, HReg **arr)
105     {
106        UInt i;
107     
108        /* Total number of allocable registers (all classes) */
109        *nregs =  16 /* GPRs */
110           -  1 /* r0 */
111           -  1 /* r12 register holding VG_(dispatch_ctr) */
112           -  1 /* r13 guest state pointer */
113           -  1 /* r14 link register */
114           -  1 /* r15 stack pointer */
115           + 16 /* FPRs */
116           ;
117     
118        *arr = LibVEX_Alloc(*nregs * sizeof(HReg));
119     
120        i = 0;
121     
122        /* GPR0 is not available because it is interpreted as 0, when used
123           as a base or index register. */
124        (*arr)[i++] = mkHReg(1,  HRcInt64, False);
125        (*arr)[i++] = mkHReg(2,  HRcInt64, False);
126        (*arr)[i++] = mkHReg(3,  HRcInt64, False);
127        (*arr)[i++] = mkHReg(4,  HRcInt64, False);
128        (*arr)[i++] = mkHReg(5,  HRcInt64, False);
129        (*arr)[i++] = mkHReg(6,  HRcInt64, False);
130        (*arr)[i++] = mkHReg(7,  HRcInt64, False);
131        (*arr)[i++] = mkHReg(8,  HRcInt64, False);
132        (*arr)[i++] = mkHReg(9,  HRcInt64, False);
133        /* GPR10 and GPR11 are used for instructions that use register pairs.
134           Otherwise, they are available to the allocator */
135        (*arr)[i++] = mkHReg(10, HRcInt64, False);
136        (*arr)[i++] = mkHReg(11, HRcInt64, False);
137        /* GPR12 is not available because it caches VG_(dispatch_ctr) */
138        /* GPR13 is not available because it is used as guest state pointer */
139        /* GPR14 is not available because it is used as link register */
140        /* GPR15 is not available because it is used as stack pointer */
141     
142        /* Add the available real (non-virtual) FPRs */
143        (*arr)[i++] = mkHReg(0,  HRcFlt64, False);
144        (*arr)[i++] = mkHReg(1,  HRcFlt64, False);
145        (*arr)[i++] = mkHReg(2,  HRcFlt64, False);
146        (*arr)[i++] = mkHReg(3,  HRcFlt64, False);
147        (*arr)[i++] = mkHReg(4,  HRcFlt64, False);
148        (*arr)[i++] = mkHReg(5,  HRcFlt64, False);
149        (*arr)[i++] = mkHReg(6,  HRcFlt64, False);
150        (*arr)[i++] = mkHReg(7,  HRcFlt64, False);
151        (*arr)[i++] = mkHReg(8,  HRcFlt64, False);
152        (*arr)[i++] = mkHReg(9,  HRcFlt64, False);
153        (*arr)[i++] = mkHReg(10, HRcFlt64, False);
154        (*arr)[i++] = mkHReg(11, HRcFlt64, False);
155        (*arr)[i++] = mkHReg(12, HRcFlt64, False);
156        (*arr)[i++] = mkHReg(13, HRcFlt64, False);
157        (*arr)[i++] = mkHReg(14, HRcFlt64, False);
158        (*arr)[i++] = mkHReg(15, HRcFlt64, False);
159        /* FPR12 - FPR15 are also used as register pairs for 128-bit
160           floating point operations */
161     }
162

164     /* Return the real register that holds the guest state pointer */
165     HReg
166     s390_hreg_guest_state_pointer(void)
167     {
168        return mkHReg(S390_REGNO_GUEST_STATE_POINTER, HRcInt64, False);
169     }
170     
171     /* Is VALUE within the domain of a 20-bit signed integer. */
172     static __inline__ Bool
173     fits_signed_20bit(Int value)
174     {
175        return ((value << 12) >> 12) == value;
176     }
177     
178     
179     /* Is VALUE within the domain of a 12-bit unsigned integer. */
180     static __inline__ Bool
181     fits_unsigned_12bit(Int value)
182     {
183        return (value & 0xFFF) == value;
184     }

186     /*------------------------------------------------------------*/
187     /*--- Addressing modes (amodes)                            ---*/
188     /*------------------------------------------------------------*/
189     
190     /* Construct a b12 amode. */
191     s390_amode *
192     s390_amode_b12(Int d, HReg b)
193     {
194        s390_amode *am = LibVEX_Alloc(sizeof(s390_amode));
195     
196        vassert(fits_unsigned_12bit(d));
197     
198        am->tag = S390_AMODE_B12;
199        am->d = d;
200        am->b = b;
201        am->x = 0;  /* hregNumber(0) == 0 */
202     
203        return am;
204     }
205     
206     
207     /* Construct a b20 amode. */
208     s390_amode *
209     s390_amode_b20(Int d, HReg b)
210     {
211        s390_amode *am = LibVEX_Alloc(sizeof(s390_amode));
212     
213        vassert(fits_signed_20bit(d));
214     
215        am->tag = S390_AMODE_B20;
216        am->d = d;
217        am->b = b;
218        am->x = 0;  /* hregNumber(0) == 0 */
219     
220        return am;
221     }
222     
223     
224     /* Construct a bx12 amode. */
225     s390_amode *
226     s390_amode_bx12(Int d, HReg b, HReg x)
227     {
228        s390_amode *am = LibVEX_Alloc(sizeof(s390_amode));
229     
230        vassert(fits_unsigned_12bit(d));
231        vassert(b != 0);
232        vassert(x != 0);
233     
234        am->tag = S390_AMODE_BX12;
235        am->d = d;
236        am->b = b;
237        am->x = x;
238     
239        return am;
240     }
241     
242     
243     /* Construct a bx20 amode. */
244     s390_amode *
245     s390_amode_bx20(Int d, HReg b, HReg x)
246     {
247        s390_amode *am = LibVEX_Alloc(sizeof(s390_amode));
248     
249        vassert(fits_signed_20bit(d));
250        vassert(b != 0);
251        vassert(x != 0);
252     
253        am->tag = S390_AMODE_BX20;
254        am->d = d;
255        am->b = b;
256        am->x = x;
257     
258        return am;
259     }
260     
261     
262     /* Construct an AMODE for accessing the guest state at OFFSET */
263     s390_amode *
264     s390_amode_for_guest_state(Int offset)
265     {
266        if (fits_unsigned_12bit(offset))
267           return s390_amode_b12(offset, s390_hreg_guest_state_pointer());
268        if (fits_signed_20bit(offset))
269           return s390_amode_b20(offset, s390_hreg_guest_state_pointer());
270     
271        vpanic("invalid guest state offset");
272     }
273     
274     
275     /* Decompile the given amode into a static buffer and return it. */
276     const HChar *
277     s390_amode_as_string(const s390_amode *am)
278     {
279        static HChar buf[30];
280        HChar *p;
281     
282        buf[0] = '\0';
283        p = buf;
284     
285        switch (am->tag) {
286        case S390_AMODE_B12:
287        case S390_AMODE_B20:
288           vex_sprintf(p, "%d(%s)", am->d, s390_hreg_as_string(am->b));
289           break;
290     
291        case S390_AMODE_BX12:
292        case S390_AMODE_BX20:
293           /* s390_hreg_as_string returns pointer to local buffer. Need to
294              split this into two printfs */
295           p += vex_sprintf(p, "%d(%s,", am->d, s390_hreg_as_string(am->x));
296           vex_sprintf(p, "%s)", s390_hreg_as_string(am->b));
297           break;
298     
299        default:
300           vpanic("s390_amode_as_string");
301        }
302     
303        return buf;
304     }
305     
306     
307     /* Helper function for s390_amode_is_sane */
308     static __inline__ Bool
309     is_virtual_gpr(HReg reg)
310     {
311        return hregIsVirtual(reg) && hregClass(reg) == HRcInt64;
312     }
313     
314     
315     /* Sanity check for an amode */
316     Bool
317     s390_amode_is_sane(const s390_amode *am)
318     {
319        switch (am->tag) {
320        case S390_AMODE_B12:
321           return is_virtual_gpr(am->b) && fits_unsigned_12bit(am->d);
322     
323        case S390_AMODE_B20:
324           return is_virtual_gpr(am->b) && fits_signed_20bit(am->d);
325     
326        case S390_AMODE_BX12:
327           return is_virtual_gpr(am->b) && is_virtual_gpr(am->x) &&
328                  fits_unsigned_12bit(am->d);
329     
330        case S390_AMODE_BX20:
331           return is_virtual_gpr(am->b) && is_virtual_gpr(am->x) &&
332                  fits_signed_20bit(am->d);
333     
334        default:
335           vpanic("s390_amode_is_sane");
336        }
337     }
338     
339     
340     /* Record the register use of an amode */
341     void
342     s390_amode_get_reg_usage(HRegUsage *u, const s390_amode *am)
343     {
344        switch (am->tag) {
345        case S390_AMODE_B12:
346        case S390_AMODE_B20:
347           addHRegUse(u, HRmRead, am->b);
348           return;
349     
350        case S390_AMODE_BX12:
351        case S390_AMODE_BX20:
352           addHRegUse(u, HRmRead, am->b);
353           addHRegUse(u, HRmRead, am->x);
354           return;
355     
356        default:
357           vpanic("s390_amode_get_reg_usage");
358        }
359     }
360     
361     
362     void
363     s390_amode_map_regs(HRegRemap *m, s390_amode *am)
364     {
365        switch (am->tag) {
366        case S390_AMODE_B12:
367        case S390_AMODE_B20:
368           am->b = lookupHRegRemap(m, am->b);
369           return;
370     
371        case S390_AMODE_BX12:
372        case S390_AMODE_BX20:
373           am->b = lookupHRegRemap(m, am->b);
374           am->x = lookupHRegRemap(m, am->x);
375           return;
376     
377        default:
378           vpanic("s390_amode_map_regs");
379        }
380     }

431     /* Figure out if the given insn represents a reg-reg move, and if so
432        assign the source and destination to *src and *dst.  If in doubt say No.
433        Used by the register allocator to do move coalescing. */
434     Bool
435     isMove_S390Instr(struct s390_insn *insn, HReg *src, HReg *dst)
436     {
437        return s390_insn_is_reg_reg_move(insn, src, dst);
438     }

440     
441     /* Generate s390 spill/reload instructions under the direction of the
442        register allocator.  Note it's critical these don't write the
443        condition codes. This is like an Ist_Put */
444     void
445     genSpill_S390(HInstr **i1, HInstr **i2, HReg rreg, Int offsetB, Bool mode64)
446     {
447        s390_amode *am;
448     
449        vassert(offsetB >= 0);
450        vassert(offsetB <= (1 << 12));  /* because we use b12 amode */
451        vassert(!hregIsVirtual(rreg));
452     
453        *i1 = *i2 = NULL;
454     
455        am = s390_amode_for_guest_state(offsetB);
456     
457        switch (hregClass(rreg)) {
458        case HRcInt64:
459        case HRcFlt64:
460           *i1 = s390_insn_store(8, am, rreg);
461           return;
462     
463        default:
464           ppHRegClass(hregClass(rreg));
465           vpanic("genSpill_S390: unimplemented regclass");
466        }
467     }
468     
469     
470     /* This is like an Iex_Get */
471     void
472     genReload_S390(HInstr **i1, HInstr **i2, HReg rreg, Int offsetB, Bool mode64)
473     {
474        s390_amode *am;
475     
476        vassert(offsetB >= 0);
477        vassert(offsetB <= (1 << 12));  /* because we use b12 amode */
478        vassert(!hregIsVirtual(rreg));
479     
480        *i1 = *i2 = NULL;
481     
482        am = s390_amode_for_guest_state(offsetB);
483     
484        switch (hregClass(rreg)) {
485        case HRcInt64:
486        case HRcFlt64:
487           *i1 = s390_insn_load(8, rreg, am);
488           return;
489     
490        default:
491           ppHRegClass(hregClass(rreg));
492           vpanic("genReload_S390: unimplemented regclass");
493        }
494     }
495     
496     /* Helper function for s390_insn_get_reg_usage */
497     static void
498     s390_opnd_RMI_get_reg_usage(HRegUsage *u, s390_opnd_RMI op)
499     {
500        switch (op.tag) {
501        case S390_OPND_REG:
502           addHRegUse(u, HRmRead, op.variant.reg);
503           break;
504     
505        case S390_OPND_AMODE:
506           s390_amode_get_reg_usage(u, op.variant.am);
507           break;
508     
509        case S390_OPND_IMMEDIATE:
510           break;
511     
512        default:
513           vpanic("s390_opnd_RMI_get_reg_usage");
514        }
515     }
516     
517     
518     /* Tell the register allocator how the given insn uses the registers */
519     void
520     s390_insn_get_reg_usage(HRegUsage *u, const s390_insn *insn)
521     {
522        initHRegUsage(u);
523     
524        switch (insn->tag) {
525        case S390_INSN_LOAD:
526           addHRegUse(u, HRmWrite, insn->variant.load.dst);
527           s390_amode_get_reg_usage(u, insn->variant.load.src);
528           break;
529     
530        case S390_INSN_LOAD_IMMEDIATE:
531           addHRegUse(u, HRmWrite, insn->variant.load_immediate.dst);
532           break;
533     
534        case S390_INSN_STORE:
535           addHRegUse(u, HRmRead, insn->variant.store.src);
536           s390_amode_get_reg_usage(u, insn->variant.store.dst);
537           break;
538     
539        case S390_INSN_MOVE:
540           addHRegUse(u, HRmRead,  insn->variant.move.src);
541           addHRegUse(u, HRmWrite, insn->variant.move.dst);
542           break;
543     
544        case S390_INSN_COND_MOVE:
545           s390_opnd_RMI_get_reg_usage(u, insn->variant.cond_move.src);
546           addHRegUse(u, HRmWrite, insn->variant.cond_move.dst);
547           break;
548     
549        case S390_INSN_ALU:
550           addHRegUse(u, HRmWrite, insn->variant.alu.dst);
551           addHRegUse(u, HRmRead,  insn->variant.alu.dst);  /* op1 */
552           s390_opnd_RMI_get_reg_usage(u, insn->variant.alu.op2);
553           break;
554     
555        case S390_INSN_MUL:
556           addHRegUse(u, HRmRead,  insn->variant.mul.dst_lo);  /* op1 */
557           addHRegUse(u, HRmWrite, insn->variant.mul.dst_lo);
558           addHRegUse(u, HRmWrite, insn->variant.mul.dst_hi);
559           s390_opnd_RMI_get_reg_usage(u, insn->variant.mul.op2);
560           break;
561     
562        case S390_INSN_DIV:
563           addHRegUse(u, HRmRead,  insn->variant.div.op1_lo);
564           addHRegUse(u, HRmRead,  insn->variant.div.op1_hi);
565           addHRegUse(u, HRmWrite, insn->variant.div.op1_lo);
566           addHRegUse(u, HRmWrite, insn->variant.div.op1_hi);
567           s390_opnd_RMI_get_reg_usage(u, insn->variant.div.op2);
568           break;
569     
570        case S390_INSN_DIVS:
571           addHRegUse(u, HRmRead,  insn->variant.divs.op1);
572           addHRegUse(u, HRmWrite, insn->variant.divs.op1); /* quotient */
573           addHRegUse(u, HRmWrite, insn->variant.divs.rem); /* remainder */
574           s390_opnd_RMI_get_reg_usage(u, insn->variant.divs.op2);
575           break;
576     
577        case S390_INSN_CLZ:
578           addHRegUse(u, HRmWrite, insn->variant.clz.num_bits);
579           addHRegUse(u, HRmWrite, insn->variant.clz.clobber);
580           s390_opnd_RMI_get_reg_usage(u, insn->variant.clz.src);
581           break;
582     
583        case S390_INSN_UNOP:
584           addHRegUse(u, HRmWrite, insn->variant.unop.dst);
585           s390_opnd_RMI_get_reg_usage(u, insn->variant.unop.src);
586           break;
587     
588        case S390_INSN_TEST:
589           s390_opnd_RMI_get_reg_usage(u, insn->variant.test.src);
590           break;
591     
592        case S390_INSN_CC2BOOL:
593           addHRegUse(u, HRmWrite, insn->variant.cc2bool.dst);
594           break;
595     
596        case S390_INSN_CAS:
597           addHRegUse(u, HRmRead,  insn->variant.cas.op1);
598           s390_amode_get_reg_usage(u, insn->variant.cas.op2);
599           addHRegUse(u, HRmRead,  insn->variant.cas.op3);
600           addHRegUse(u, HRmWrite,  insn->variant.cas.old_mem);
601           break;
602     
603        case S390_INSN_COMPARE:
604           addHRegUse(u, HRmRead, insn->variant.compare.src1);
605           s390_opnd_RMI_get_reg_usage(u, insn->variant.compare.src2);
606           break;
607     
608        case S390_INSN_BRANCH:
609           s390_opnd_RMI_get_reg_usage(u, insn->variant.branch.dst);
610           /* The destination address is loaded into S390_REGNO_RETURN_VALUE.
611              See s390_insn_branch_emit. */
612           addHRegUse(u, HRmWrite,
613                      mkHReg(S390_REGNO_RETURN_VALUE, HRcInt64, False));
614           break;
615     
616        case S390_INSN_HELPER_CALL: {
617           UInt i;
618     
619           /* Assume that all volatile registers are clobbered. ABI says,
620              volatile registers are: r0 - r5. Valgrind's register allocator
621              does not know about r0, so we can leave that out */
622           for (i = 1; i <= 5; ++i) {
623              addHRegUse(u, HRmWrite, mkHReg(i, HRcInt64, False));
624           }
625     
626           /* Ditto for floating point registers. f0 - f7 are volatile */
627           for (i = 0; i <= 7; ++i) {
628              addHRegUse(u, HRmWrite, mkHReg(i, HRcFlt64, False));
629           }
630     
631           /* The registers that are used for passing arguments will be read.
632              Not all of them may, but in general we need to assume that. */
633           for (i = 0; i < insn->variant.helper_call.num_args; ++i) {
634              addHRegUse(u, HRmRead, mkHReg(s390_gprno_from_arg_index(i),
635                                            HRcInt64, False));
636           }
637     
638           /* s390_insn_helper_call_emit also reads / writes the link register
639              and stack pointer. But those registers are not visible to the
640              register allocator. So we don't need to do anything for them. */
641           break;
642        }
643     
644        case S390_INSN_BFP_TRIOP:
645           addHRegUse(u, HRmWrite, insn->variant.bfp_triop.dst);
646           addHRegUse(u, HRmRead,  insn->variant.bfp_triop.dst);  /* first */
647           addHRegUse(u, HRmRead,  insn->variant.bfp_triop.op2);  /* second */
648           addHRegUse(u, HRmRead,  insn->variant.bfp_triop.op3);  /* third */
649           break;
650     
651        case S390_INSN_BFP_BINOP:
652           addHRegUse(u, HRmWrite, insn->variant.bfp_binop.dst);
653           addHRegUse(u, HRmRead,  insn->variant.bfp_binop.dst);  /* left */
654           addHRegUse(u, HRmRead,  insn->variant.bfp_binop.op2);  /* right */
655           break;
656     
657        case S390_INSN_BFP_UNOP:
658           addHRegUse(u, HRmWrite, insn->variant.bfp_unop.dst);
659           addHRegUse(u, HRmRead,  insn->variant.bfp_unop.op);  /* operand */
660           break;
661     
662        case S390_INSN_BFP_COMPARE:
663           addHRegUse(u, HRmWrite, insn->variant.bfp_compare.dst);
664           addHRegUse(u, HRmRead,  insn->variant.bfp_compare.op1);  /* left */
665           addHRegUse(u, HRmRead,  insn->variant.bfp_compare.op2);  /* right */
666           break;
667     
668        case S390_INSN_BFP128_BINOP:
669           addHRegUse(u, HRmWrite, insn->variant.bfp128_binop.dst_hi);
670           addHRegUse(u, HRmWrite, insn->variant.bfp128_binop.dst_lo);
671           addHRegUse(u, HRmRead,  insn->variant.bfp128_binop.dst_hi);  /* left */
672           addHRegUse(u, HRmRead,  insn->variant.bfp128_binop.dst_lo);  /* left */
673           addHRegUse(u, HRmRead,  insn->variant.bfp128_binop.op2_hi);  /* right */
674           addHRegUse(u, HRmRead,  insn->variant.bfp128_binop.op2_lo);  /* right */
675           break;
676     
677        case S390_INSN_BFP128_COMPARE:
678           addHRegUse(u, HRmWrite, insn->variant.bfp128_compare.dst);
679           addHRegUse(u, HRmRead,  insn->variant.bfp128_compare.op1_hi);  /* left */
680           addHRegUse(u, HRmRead,  insn->variant.bfp128_compare.op1_lo);  /* left */
681           addHRegUse(u, HRmRead,  insn->variant.bfp128_compare.op2_hi);  /* right */
682           addHRegUse(u, HRmRead,  insn->variant.bfp128_compare.op2_lo);  /* right */
683           break;
684     
685        case S390_INSN_BFP128_UNOP:
686           addHRegUse(u, HRmWrite, insn->variant.bfp128_unop.dst_hi);
687           addHRegUse(u, HRmWrite, insn->variant.bfp128_unop.dst_lo);
688           addHRegUse(u, HRmRead,  insn->variant.bfp128_unop.op_hi);
689           addHRegUse(u, HRmRead,  insn->variant.bfp128_unop.op_lo);
690           break;
691     
692        case S390_INSN_BFP128_CONVERT_TO:
693           addHRegUse(u, HRmWrite, insn->variant.bfp128_unop.dst_hi);
694           addHRegUse(u, HRmWrite, insn->variant.bfp128_unop.dst_lo);
695           addHRegUse(u, HRmRead,  insn->variant.bfp128_unop.op_hi);
696           break;
697     
698        case S390_INSN_BFP128_CONVERT_FROM:
699           addHRegUse(u, HRmWrite, insn->variant.bfp128_unop.dst_hi);
700           addHRegUse(u, HRmRead,  insn->variant.bfp128_unop.op_hi);
701           addHRegUse(u, HRmRead,  insn->variant.bfp128_unop.op_lo);
702           break;
703     
704        default:
705           vpanic("s390_insn_get_reg_usage");
706        }
707     }
708     
709     
710     /* Helper function for s390_insn_map_regs */
711     static void
712     s390_opnd_RMI_map_regs(HRegRemap *m, s390_opnd_RMI *op)
713     {
714        switch (op->tag) {
715        case S390_OPND_REG:
716           op->variant.reg = lookupHRegRemap(m, op->variant.reg);
717           break;
718     
719        case S390_OPND_IMMEDIATE:
720           break;
721     
722        case S390_OPND_AMODE:
723           s390_amode_map_regs(m, op->variant.am);
724           break;
725     
726        default:
727           vpanic("s390_opnd_RMI_map_regs");
728        }
729     }
730     
731     
732     void
733     s390_insn_map_regs(HRegRemap *m, s390_insn *insn)
734     {
735        switch (insn->tag) {
736        case S390_INSN_LOAD:
737           insn->variant.load.dst = lookupHRegRemap(m, insn->variant.load.dst);
738           s390_amode_map_regs(m, insn->variant.load.src);
739           break;
740     
741        case S390_INSN_STORE:
742           s390_amode_map_regs(m, insn->variant.store.dst);
743           insn->variant.store.src = lookupHRegRemap(m, insn->variant.store.src);
744           break;
745     
746        case S390_INSN_MOVE:
747           insn->variant.move.dst = lookupHRegRemap(m, insn->variant.move.dst);
748           insn->variant.move.src = lookupHRegRemap(m, insn->variant.move.src);
749           break;
750     
751        case S390_INSN_COND_MOVE:
752           insn->variant.cond_move.dst = lookupHRegRemap(m, insn->variant.cond_move.dst);
753           s390_opnd_RMI_map_regs(m, &insn->variant.cond_move.src);
754           break;
755     
756        case S390_INSN_LOAD_IMMEDIATE:
757           insn->variant.load_immediate.dst =
758              lookupHRegRemap(m, insn->variant.load_immediate.dst);
759           break;
760     
761        case S390_INSN_ALU:
762           insn->variant.alu.dst = lookupHRegRemap(m, insn->variant.alu.dst);
763           s390_opnd_RMI_map_regs(m, &insn->variant.alu.op2);
764           break;
765     
766        case S390_INSN_MUL:
767           insn->variant.mul.dst_hi = lookupHRegRemap(m, insn->variant.mul.dst_hi);
768           insn->variant.mul.dst_lo = lookupHRegRemap(m, insn->variant.mul.dst_lo);
769           s390_opnd_RMI_map_regs(m, &insn->variant.mul.op2);
770           break;
771     
772        case S390_INSN_DIV:
773           insn->variant.div.op1_hi = lookupHRegRemap(m, insn->variant.div.op1_hi);
774           insn->variant.div.op1_lo = lookupHRegRemap(m, insn->variant.div.op1_lo);
775           s390_opnd_RMI_map_regs(m, &insn->variant.div.op2);
776           break;
777     
778        case S390_INSN_DIVS:
779           insn->variant.divs.op1 = lookupHRegRemap(m, insn->variant.divs.op1);
780           insn->variant.divs.rem = lookupHRegRemap(m, insn->variant.divs.rem);
781           s390_opnd_RMI_map_regs(m, &insn->variant.divs.op2);
782           break;
783     
784        case S390_INSN_CLZ:
785           insn->variant.clz.num_bits = lookupHRegRemap(m, insn->variant.clz.num_bits);
786           insn->variant.clz.clobber  = lookupHRegRemap(m, insn->variant.clz.clobber);
787           s390_opnd_RMI_map_regs(m, &insn->variant.clz.src);
788           break;
789     
790        case S390_INSN_UNOP:
791           insn->variant.unop.dst = lookupHRegRemap(m, insn->variant.unop.dst);
792           s390_opnd_RMI_map_regs(m, &insn->variant.unop.src);
793           break;
794     
795        case S390_INSN_TEST:
796           s390_opnd_RMI_map_regs(m, &insn->variant.test.src);
797           break;
798     
799        case S390_INSN_CC2BOOL:
800           insn->variant.cc2bool.dst = lookupHRegRemap(m, insn->variant.cc2bool.dst);
801           break;
802     
803        case S390_INSN_CAS:
804           insn->variant.cas.op1 = lookupHRegRemap(m, insn->variant.cas.op1);
805           s390_amode_map_regs(m, insn->variant.cas.op2);
806           insn->variant.cas.op3 = lookupHRegRemap(m, insn->variant.cas.op3);
807           insn->variant.cas.old_mem = lookupHRegRemap(m, insn->variant.cas.old_mem);
808           break;
809     
810        case S390_INSN_COMPARE:
811           insn->variant.compare.src1 = lookupHRegRemap(m, insn->variant.compare.src1);
812           s390_opnd_RMI_map_regs(m, &insn->variant.compare.src2);
813           break;
814     
815        case S390_INSN_BRANCH:
816           s390_opnd_RMI_map_regs(m, &insn->variant.branch.dst);
817           /* No need to map S390_REGNO_RETURN_VALUE. It's not virtual */
818           break;
819     
820        case S390_INSN_HELPER_CALL:
821           /* s390_insn_helper_call_emit also reads / writes the link register
822              and stack pointer. But those registers are not visible to the
823              register allocator. So we don't need to do anything for them.
824              As for the arguments of the helper call -- they will be loaded into
825              non-virtual registers. Again, we don't need to do anything for those
826              here. */
827           break;
828     
829        case S390_INSN_BFP_TRIOP:
830           insn->variant.bfp_triop.dst = lookupHRegRemap(m, insn->variant.bfp_triop.dst);
831           insn->variant.bfp_triop.op2 = lookupHRegRemap(m, insn->variant.bfp_triop.op2);
832           insn->variant.bfp_triop.op3 = lookupHRegRemap(m, insn->variant.bfp_triop.op3);
833           break;
834     
835        case S390_INSN_BFP_BINOP:
836           insn->variant.bfp_binop.dst = lookupHRegRemap(m, insn->variant.bfp_binop.dst);
837           insn->variant.bfp_binop.op2 = lookupHRegRemap(m, insn->variant.bfp_binop.op2);
838           break;
839     
840        case S390_INSN_BFP_UNOP:
841           insn->variant.bfp_unop.dst = lookupHRegRemap(m, insn->variant.bfp_unop.dst);
842           insn->variant.bfp_unop.op  = lookupHRegRemap(m, insn->variant.bfp_unop.op);
843           break;
844     
845        case S390_INSN_BFP_COMPARE:
846           insn->variant.bfp_compare.dst = lookupHRegRemap(m, insn->variant.bfp_compare.dst);
847           insn->variant.bfp_compare.op1 = lookupHRegRemap(m, insn->variant.bfp_compare.op1);
848           insn->variant.bfp_compare.op2 = lookupHRegRemap(m, insn->variant.bfp_compare.op2);
849           break;
850     
851        case S390_INSN_BFP128_BINOP:
852           insn->variant.bfp128_binop.dst_hi =
853              lookupHRegRemap(m, insn->variant.bfp128_binop.dst_hi);
854           insn->variant.bfp128_binop.dst_lo =
855              lookupHRegRemap(m, insn->variant.bfp128_binop.dst_lo);
856           insn->variant.bfp128_binop.op2_hi =
857              lookupHRegRemap(m, insn->variant.bfp128_binop.op2_hi);
858           insn->variant.bfp128_binop.op2_lo =
859              lookupHRegRemap(m, insn->variant.bfp128_binop.op2_lo);
860           break;
861     
862        case S390_INSN_BFP128_COMPARE:
863           insn->variant.bfp128_compare.dst =
864              lookupHRegRemap(m, insn->variant.bfp128_compare.dst);
865           insn->variant.bfp128_compare.op1_hi =
866              lookupHRegRemap(m, insn->variant.bfp128_compare.op1_hi);
867           insn->variant.bfp128_compare.op1_lo =
868              lookupHRegRemap(m, insn->variant.bfp128_compare.op1_lo);
869           insn->variant.bfp128_compare.op2_hi =
870              lookupHRegRemap(m, insn->variant.bfp128_compare.op2_hi);
871           insn->variant.bfp128_compare.op2_lo =
872              lookupHRegRemap(m, insn->variant.bfp128_compare.op2_lo);
873           break;
874     
875        case S390_INSN_BFP128_UNOP:
876           insn->variant.bfp128_unop.dst_hi =
877              lookupHRegRemap(m, insn->variant.bfp128_unop.dst_hi);
878           insn->variant.bfp128_unop.dst_lo =
879              lookupHRegRemap(m, insn->variant.bfp128_unop.dst_lo);
880           insn->variant.bfp128_unop.op_hi =
881              lookupHRegRemap(m, insn->variant.bfp128_unop.op_hi);
882           insn->variant.bfp128_unop.op_lo =
883              lookupHRegRemap(m, insn->variant.bfp128_unop.op_lo);
884           break;
885     
886        case S390_INSN_BFP128_CONVERT_TO:
887           insn->variant.bfp128_unop.dst_hi =
888              lookupHRegRemap(m, insn->variant.bfp128_unop.dst_hi);
889           insn->variant.bfp128_unop.dst_lo =
890              lookupHRegRemap(m, insn->variant.bfp128_unop.dst_lo);
891           insn->variant.bfp128_unop.op_hi =
892              lookupHRegRemap(m, insn->variant.bfp128_unop.op_hi);
893           break;
894     
895        case S390_INSN_BFP128_CONVERT_FROM:
896           insn->variant.bfp128_unop.dst_hi =
897              lookupHRegRemap(m, insn->variant.bfp128_unop.dst_hi);
898           insn->variant.bfp128_unop.op_hi =
899              lookupHRegRemap(m, insn->variant.bfp128_unop.op_hi);
900           insn->variant.bfp128_unop.op_lo =
901              lookupHRegRemap(m, insn->variant.bfp128_unop.op_lo);
902           break;
903     
904        default:
905           vpanic("s390_insn_map_regs");
906        }
907     }
908     
909     
910     /* Return True, if INSN is a move between two registers of the same class.
911        In that case assign the source and destination registers to SRC and DST,
912        respectively. */
913     Bool
914     s390_insn_is_reg_reg_move(const s390_insn *insn, HReg *src, HReg *dst)
915     {
916        if (insn->tag == S390_INSN_MOVE &&
917            hregClass(insn->variant.move.src) == hregClass(insn->variant.move.dst)) {
918           *src = insn->variant.move.src;
919           *dst = insn->variant.move.dst;
920           return True;
921        }
922     
923        return False;
924     }

927     #undef likely
928     #undef unlikely
929     #define likely(x)       __builtin_expect(!!(x), 1)
930     #define unlikely(x)     __builtin_expect(!!(x), 0)
931     
932     /*------------------------------------------------------------*/
933     /*--- Functions to emit a sequence of bytes                ---*/
934     /*------------------------------------------------------------*/
935     
936     
937     static __inline__ UChar *
938     emit_2bytes(UChar *p, ULong val)
939     {
940        return (UChar *)__builtin_memcpy(p, ((UChar *)&val) + 6, 2) + 2;
941     }
942     
943     
944     static __inline__ UChar *
945     emit_4bytes(UChar *p, ULong val)
946     {
947        return (UChar *)__builtin_memcpy(p, ((UChar *)&val) + 4, 4) + 4;
948     }
949     
950     
951     static __inline__ UChar *
952     emit_6bytes(UChar *p, ULong val)
953     {
954        return (UChar *)__builtin_memcpy(p, ((UChar *)&val) + 2, 6) + 6;
955     }
956     
957     
958     /*------------------------------------------------------------*/
959     /*--- Functions to emit various instruction formats        ---*/
960     /*------------------------------------------------------------*/
961     
962     
963     static UChar *
964     emit_RI(UChar *p, UInt op, UChar r1, UShort i2)
965     {
966        ULong the_insn = op;
967     
968        the_insn |= ((ULong)r1) << 20;
969        the_insn |= ((ULong)i2) << 0;
970     
971        return emit_4bytes(p, the_insn);
972     }
973     
974     
975     static UChar *
976     emit_RIL(UChar *p, ULong op, UChar r1, UInt i2)
977     {
978        ULong the_insn = op;
979     
980        the_insn |= ((ULong)r1) << 36;
981        the_insn |= ((ULong)i2) << 0;
982     
983        return emit_6bytes(p, the_insn);
984     }
985     
986     
987     static UChar *
988     emit_RR(UChar *p, UInt op, UChar r1, UChar r2)
989     {
990        ULong the_insn = op;
991     
992        the_insn |= ((ULong)r1) << 4;
993        the_insn |= ((ULong)r2) << 0;
994     
995        return emit_2bytes(p, the_insn);
996     }
997     
998     
999     static UChar *
1000     emit_RRE(UChar *p, UInt op, UChar r1, UChar r2)
1001     {
1002        ULong the_insn = op;
1003     
1004        the_insn |= ((ULong)r1) << 4;
1005        the_insn |= ((ULong)r2) << 0;
1006     
1007        return emit_4bytes(p, the_insn);
1008     }
1009     
1010     
1011     static UChar *
1012     emit_RRF(UChar *p, UInt op, UChar r1, UChar r3, UChar r2)
1013     {
1014        ULong the_insn = op;
1015     
1016        the_insn |= ((ULong)r1) << 12;
1017        the_insn |= ((ULong)r3) << 4;
1018        the_insn |= ((ULong)r2) << 0;
1019     
1020        return emit_4bytes(p, the_insn);
1021     }
1022     
1023     
1024     static UChar *
1025     emit_RRF3(UChar *p, UInt op, UChar r3, UChar r1, UChar r2)
1026     {
1027        ULong the_insn = op;
1028     
1029        the_insn |= ((ULong)r3) << 12;
1030        the_insn |= ((ULong)r1) << 4;
1031        the_insn |= ((ULong)r2) << 0;
1032     
1033        return emit_4bytes(p, the_insn);
1034     }
1035     
1036     
1037     static UChar *
1038     emit_RS(UChar *p, UInt op, UChar r1, UChar r3, UChar b2, UShort d2)
1039     {
1040        ULong the_insn = op;
1041     
1042        the_insn |= ((ULong)r1) << 20;
1043        the_insn |= ((ULong)r3) << 16;
1044        the_insn |= ((ULong)b2) << 12;
1045        the_insn |= ((ULong)d2) << 0;
1046     
1047        return emit_4bytes(p, the_insn);
1048     }
1049     
1050     
1051     static UChar *
1052     emit_RSY(UChar *p, ULong op, UChar r1, UChar r3, UChar b2, UShort dl2, UChar dh2)
1053     {
1054        ULong the_insn = op;
1055     
1056        the_insn |= ((ULong)r1) << 36;
1057        the_insn |= ((ULong)r3) << 32;
1058        the_insn |= ((ULong)b2) << 28;
1059        the_insn |= ((ULong)dl2) << 16;
1060        the_insn |= ((ULong)dh2) << 8;
1061     
1062        return emit_6bytes(p, the_insn);
1063     }
1064     
1065     
1066     static UChar *
1067     emit_RX(UChar *p, UInt op, UChar r1, UChar x2, UChar b2, UShort d2)
1068     {
1069        ULong the_insn = op;
1070     
1071        the_insn |= ((ULong)r1) << 20;
1072        the_insn |= ((ULong)x2) << 16;
1073        the_insn |= ((ULong)b2) << 12;
1074        the_insn |= ((ULong)d2) << 0;
1075     
1076        return emit_4bytes(p, the_insn);
1077     }
1078     
1079     
1080     static UChar *
1081     emit_RXY(UChar *p, ULong op, UChar r1, UChar x2, UChar b2, UShort dl2, UChar dh2)
1082     {
1083        ULong the_insn = op;
1084     
1085        the_insn |= ((ULong)r1) << 36;
1086        the_insn |= ((ULong)x2) << 32;
1087        the_insn |= ((ULong)b2) << 28;
1088        the_insn |= ((ULong)dl2) << 16;
1089        the_insn |= ((ULong)dh2) << 8;
1090     
1091        return emit_6bytes(p, the_insn);
1092     }
1093     
1094     
1095     static UChar *
1096     emit_S(UChar *p, UInt op, UChar b2, UShort d2)
1097     {
1098        ULong the_insn = op;
1099     
1100        the_insn |= ((ULong)b2) << 12;
1101        the_insn |= ((ULong)d2) << 0;
1102     
1103        return emit_4bytes(p, the_insn);
1104     }

1107     /*------------------------------------------------------------*/
1108     /*--- Functions to emit particular instructions            ---*/
1109     /*------------------------------------------------------------*/
1110     
1111     
1112     static UChar *
1113     s390_emit_AR(UChar *p, UChar r1, UChar r2)
1114     {
1115        if (unlikely(vex_traceflags & VEX_TRACE_ASM))
1116           s390_disasm(ENC3(MNM, GPR, GPR), "ar", r1, r2);
1117     
1118        return emit_RR(p, 0x1a00, r1, r2);
1119     }
1120     
1121     
1122     static UChar *
1123     s390_emit_AGR(UChar *p, UChar r1, UChar r2)
1124     {
1125        if (unlikely(vex_traceflags & VEX_TRACE_ASM))
1126           s390_disasm(ENC3(MNM, GPR, GPR), "agr", r1, r2);
1127     
1128        return emit_RRE(p, 0xb9080000, r1, r2);
1129     }
1130     
1131     
1132     static UChar *
1133     s390_emit_A(UChar *p, UChar r1, UChar x2, UChar b2, UShort d2)

3220     
3221     /* For both 32-bit and 64-bit clients we can use the instructions that
3222        were available on z900. See binutils/opcodes/s390-opc.txt
3223     
3224        Note, that entering a wrapper for a z/arch instruction does not
3225        imply that the client is a 64-bit client. It only means that this
3226        instruction is a good match for the expression at hand.
3227     */
3228     
3229     /* Provide a symbolic name for register "R0" */
3230     #define R0 0
3231     
3232     /* Split up a 20-bit displacement into its high and low piece
3233        suitable for passing as function arguments */
3234     #define DISP20(d) ((d) & 0xFFF), (((d) >> 12) & 0xFF)
3235     
3236     /*---------------------------------------------------------------*/
3237     /*--- Helper functions                                        ---*/
3238     /*---------------------------------------------------------------*/
3239     
3240     static __inline__ Bool
3241     uint_fits_signed_16bit(UInt val)
3242     {
3243        int v = val & 0xFFFFu;
3244     
3245        /* sign extend */
3246        v = (v << 16) >> 16;
3247     
3248        return val == (UInt)v;
3249     }
3250     
3251     
3252     static __inline__ Bool
3253     ulong_fits_signed_16bit(ULong val)
3254     {
3255        Long v = val & 0xFFFFu;
3256     
3257        /* sign extend */
3258        v = (v << 48) >> 48;
3259     
3260        return val == (ULong)v;
3261     }
3262     
3263     
3264     static __inline__ Bool
3265     ulong_fits_signed_32bit(ULong val)
3266     {
3267        Long v = val & 0xFFFFFFFFu;
3268     
3269        /* sign extend */
3270        v = (v << 32) >> 32;
3271     
3272        return val == (ULong)v;
3273     }
3274     
3275     
3276     static __inline__ Bool
3277     ulong_fits_unsigned_32bit(ULong val)
3278     {
3279        return (val & 0xFFFFFFFFu) == val;
3280     }
3281     
3282     
3283     /* Load a 64-bit immediate VAL into register REG. */
3284     static UChar *
3285     s390_emit_load_64imm(UChar *p, UChar reg, ULong val)
3286     {
3287        if (ulong_fits_signed_16bit(val)) {
3288           return s390_emit_LGHI(p, reg, val);
3289        }
3290     
3291        if (s390_host_has_eimm) {
3292           if (ulong_fits_unsigned_32bit(val)) {
3293              return s390_emit_LLILF(p, reg, val);
3294           }
3295           if (ulong_fits_signed_32bit(val)) {
3296              /* LGFI's sign extension will recreate the correct 64-bit value */
3297              return s390_emit_LGFI(p, reg, val);
3298           }
3299           /* Do it in two steps: upper half [0:31] and lower half [32:63] */
3300           p =  s390_emit_IIHF(p, reg, val >> 32);
3301           return s390_emit_IILF(p, reg, val & 0xFFFFFFFF);
3302        }
3303     
3304        /* Fall back */
3305        if (ulong_fits_unsigned_32bit(val)) {
3306           p = s390_emit_LLILH(p, reg, (val >> 16) & 0xFFFF); /* sets val[32:47]
3307                                                                 val[0:31] = 0 */
3308           p = s390_emit_IILL(p, reg, val & 0xFFFF);          /* sets val[48:63] */
3309           return p;
3310        }
3311     
3312        p = s390_emit_IIHH(p, reg, (val >> 48) & 0xFFFF);
3313        p = s390_emit_IIHL(p, reg, (val >> 32) & 0xFFFF);
3314        p = s390_emit_IILH(p, reg, (val >> 16) & 0xFFFF);
3315        p = s390_emit_IILL(p, reg, val & 0xFFFF);
3316     
3317        return p;
3318     }
3319     
3320     /* Load a 32-bit immediate VAL into register REG. */
3321     static UChar *
3322     s390_emit_load_32imm(UChar *p, UChar reg, UInt val)
3323     {
3324        if (uint_fits_signed_16bit(val)) {
3325           /* LHI's sign extension will recreate the correct 32-bit value */
3326           return s390_emit_LHI(p, reg, val);
3327        }
3328        if (s390_host_has_eimm) {
3329           return s390_emit_IILF(p, reg, val);
3330        }
3331        /* val[0:15]  --> (val >> 16) & 0xFFFF
3332           val[16:31] --> val & 0xFFFF */
3333        p = s390_emit_IILH(p, reg, (val >> 16) & 0xFFFF);
3334        return s390_emit_IILL(p, reg, val & 0xFFFF);
3335     }
3336     
3337     /*------------------------------------------------------------*/
3338     /*--- Wrapper functions                                    ---*/
3339     /*------------------------------------------------------------*/
3340     
3341     /* r1[32:63],r1+1[32:63] = r1+1[32:63] * memory[op2addr][0:31] */
3342     static UChar *
3343     s390_emit_MFYw(UChar *p, UChar r1, UChar x, UChar b,  UShort dl, UChar dh)
3344     {
3345        if (s390_host_has_gie) {
3346           return s390_emit_MFY(p, r1, x, b, dl, dh);
3347        }
3348     
3349        /* Load from memory into R0, then MULTIPLY with R1 */
3350        p = s390_emit_LY(p, R0, x, b, dl, dh);
3351        return s390_emit_MR(p, r1, R0);
3352     }
3353     
3354     /* r1[32:63] = r1[32:63] * memory[op2addr][0:15] */
3355     static UChar *
3356     s390_emit_MHYw(UChar *p, UChar r1, UChar x, UChar b,  UShort dl, UChar dh)
3357     {
3358        if (s390_host_has_gie) {
3359           return s390_emit_MHY(p, r1, x, b, dl, dh);
3360        }
3361     
3362        /* Load from memory into R0, then MULTIPLY with R1 */
3363        p = s390_emit_LHY(p, R0, x, b, dl, dh);
3364        return s390_emit_MSR(p, r1, R0);
3365     }
3366     
3367     /* r1[32:63] = r1[32:63] * i2 */
3368     static UChar *
3369     s390_emit_MSFIw(UChar *p, UChar r1, UInt i2)
3370     {
3371        if (s390_host_has_gie) {
3372           return s390_emit_MSFI(p, r1, i2);
3373        }
3374     
3375        /* Load I2 into R0; then MULTIPLY R0 with R1 */
3376        p = s390_emit_load_32imm(p, R0, i2);
3377        return s390_emit_MSR(p, r1, R0);
3378     }
3379     
3380     
3381     /* r1[32:63] = r1[32:63] & i2 */
3382     static UChar *
3383     s390_emit_NILFw(UChar *p, UChar r1, UInt i2)
3384     {
3385        if (s390_host_has_eimm) {
3386           return s390_emit_NILF(p, r1, i2);
3387        }
3388     
3389        /* Load I2 into R0; then AND R0 with R1 */
3390        p = s390_emit_load_32imm(p, R0, i2);
3391        return s390_emit_NR(p, r1, R0);
3392     }
3393     
3394     
3395     /* r1[32:63] = r1[32:63] | i2 */
3396     static UChar *
3397     s390_emit_OILFw(UChar *p, UChar r1, UInt i2)
3398     {
3399        if (s390_host_has_eimm) {
3400           return s390_emit_OILF(p, r1, i2);
3401        }
3402     
3403        /* Load I2 into R0; then AND R0 with R1 */
3404        p = s390_emit_load_32imm(p, R0, i2);
3405        return s390_emit_OR(p, r1, R0);
3406     }
3407     
3408     
3409     /* r1[32:63] = r1[32:63] ^ i2 */
3410     static UChar *
3411     s390_emit_XILFw(UChar *p, UChar r1, UInt i2)
3412     {
3413        if (s390_host_has_eimm) {
3414           return s390_emit_XILF(p, r1, i2);
3415        }
3416     
3417        /* Load I2 into R0; then AND R0 with R1 */
3418        p = s390_emit_load_32imm(p, R0, i2);
3419        return s390_emit_XR(p, r1, R0);
3420     }
3421     
3422     
3423     /*  r1[32:63] = sign_extend(r2[56:63]) */
3424     static UChar *
3425     s390_emit_LBRw(UChar *p, UChar r1, UChar r2)
3426     {
3427        if (s390_host_has_eimm) {
3428           return s390_emit_LBR(p, r1, r2);
3429        }
3430     
3431        p = s390_emit_LR(p, r1, r2);               /* r1 = r2 */
3432        p = s390_emit_SLL(p, r1, R0, 24);          /* r1 = r1 << 24  */
3433        return s390_emit_SRA(p, r1, R0, 24);       /* r1 = r1 >>a 24 */
3434     }
3435     
3436     
3437     /*  r1[0:63] = sign_extend(r2[56:63]) */
3438     static UChar *
3439     s390_emit_LGBRw(UChar *p, UChar r1, UChar r2)
3440     {
3441        if (s390_host_has_eimm) {
3442           return s390_emit_LGBR(p, r1, r2);
3443        }
3444     
3445        p = s390_emit_LR(p, r1, r2);                       /* r1 = r2 */
3446        p = s390_emit_SLLG(p, r1, r1, R0, DISP20(56));     /* r1 = r1 << 56  */
3447        return s390_emit_SRAG(p, r1, r1, R0, DISP20(56));  /* r1 = r1 >>a 56 */
3448     }
3449     
3450     
3451     /* r1[32:63] = sign_extend(r2[48:63]) */
3452     static UChar *
3453     s390_emit_LHRw(UChar *p, UChar r1, UChar r2)
3454     {
3455        if (s390_host_has_eimm) {
3456           return s390_emit_LHR(p, r1, r2);
3457        }
3458     
3459        p = s390_emit_LR(p, r1, r2);               /* r1 = r2 */
3460        p = s390_emit_SLL(p, r1, R0, 16);          /* r1 = r1 << 16  */
3461        return s390_emit_SRA(p, r1, R0, 16);       /* r1 = r1 >>a 16 */
3462     }
3463     
3464     
3465     /* r1[0:63] = sign_extend(r2[48:63]) */
3466     static UChar *
3467     s390_emit_LGHRw(UChar *p, UChar r1, UChar r2)
3468     {
3469        if (s390_host_has_eimm) {
3470           return s390_emit_LGHR(p, r1, r2);
3471        }
3472     
3473        p = s390_emit_LR(p, r1, r2);               /* r1 = r2 */
3474        p = s390_emit_SLLG(p, r1, r1, R0, DISP20(48));     /* r1 = r1 << 48  */
3475        return s390_emit_SRAG(p, r1, r1, R0, DISP20(48));  /* r1 = r1 >>a 48 */
3476     }
3477     
3478     
3479     /* r1[0:63] = sign_extend(i2) */
3480     static UChar *
3481     s390_emit_LGFIw(UChar *p, UChar r1, UInt i2)
3482     {
3483        if (s390_host_has_eimm) {
3484           return s390_emit_LGFI(p, r1, i2);
3485        }
3486     
3487        p = s390_emit_load_32imm(p, R0, i2);
3488        return s390_emit_LGFR(p, r1, R0);
3489     }
3490     
3491     
3492     /* r1[32:63] = zero_extend($r2[56:63]) */
3493     static UChar *
3494     s390_emit_LLCRw(UChar *p, UChar r1, UChar r2)
3495     {
3496        if (s390_host_has_eimm) {
3497           return s390_emit_LLCR(p, r1, r2);
3498        }
3499     
3500        p = s390_emit_LR(p, r1, r2);
3501        p = s390_emit_LHI(p, R0, 0xFF);
3502        return s390_emit_NR(p, r1, R0);
3503     }
3504

3506     /* r1[0:63] = zero_extend($r2[56:63]) */
3507     static UChar *
3508     s390_emit_LLGCRw(UChar *p, UChar r1, UChar r2)
3509     {
3510        if (s390_host_has_eimm) {
3511           return s390_emit_LLGCR(p, r1, r2);
3512        }
3513     
3514        p = s390_emit_LR(p, r1, r2);
3515        p = s390_emit_LLILL(p, R0, 0xFF);
3516        return s390_emit_NGR(p, r1, R0);
3517     }
3518     
3519     
3520     /* r1[32:63] = zero_extend(r2[48:63]) */
3521     static UChar *
3522     s390_emit_LLHRw(UChar *p, UChar r1, UChar r2)
3523     {
3524        if (s390_host_has_eimm) {
3525           return s390_emit_LLHR(p, r1, r2);
3526        }
3527     
3528        p = s390_emit_LR(p, r1, r2);
3529        p = s390_emit_LLILL(p, R0, 0xFFFF);
3530        return s390_emit_NR(p, r1, R0);
3531     }
3532     
3533     
3534     /* r1[0:63] = zero_extend(r2[48:63]) */
3535     static UChar *
3536     s390_emit_LLGHRw(UChar *p, UChar r1, UChar r2)
3537     {
3538        if (s390_host_has_eimm) {
3539           return s390_emit_LLGHR(p, r1, r2);
3540        }
3541     
3542        p = s390_emit_LR(p, r1, r2);
3543        p = s390_emit_LLILL(p, R0, 0xFFFF);
3544        return s390_emit_NGR(p, r1, R0);
3545     }
3546     
3547     
3548     /* r1[32:63] = zero_extend(mem[op2addr][0:7]) */
3549     static UChar *
3550     s390_emit_LLCw(UChar *p, UChar r1, UChar x2, UChar b2, UShort dl, UChar dh)
3551     {
3552        if (s390_host_has_eimm) {
3553           return s390_emit_LLC(p, r1, x2, b2, dl, dh);
3554        }
3555     
3556        if (dh == 0) {
3557           p = s390_emit_IC(p, r1, x2, b2, dl);
3558        } else {
3559           p = s390_emit_ICY(p, r1, x2, b2, dl, dh);
3560        }
3561        p = s390_emit_LLILL(p, R0, 0xFF);
3562        return s390_emit_NR(p, r1, R0);
3563     }
3564

3566     /* r1[32:63] = zero_extend(mem[op2addr][0:15]) */
3567     static UChar *
3568     s390_emit_LLHw(UChar *p, UChar r1, UChar x2, UChar b2, UShort dl, UChar dh)
3569     {
3570        if (s390_host_has_eimm) {
3571           return s390_emit_LLH(p, r1, x2, b2, dl, dh);
3572        }
3573     
3574        p = s390_emit_LLGH(p, r1, x2, b2, dl, dh);
3575        p = s390_emit_LLILL(p, R0, 0xFFFF);
3576        return s390_emit_NR(p, r1, R0);
3577     }

3585           return s390_emit_LLILF(p, r1, i2);
3586        }
3587     
3588        p = s390_emit_LLILH(p, r1, (i2 >> 16) & 0xFFFF);  /* i2[0:15] */
3589        return s390_emit_OILL(p, r1, i2 & 0xFFFF);
3590     }

3594     static UChar *

3597        if (s390_host_has_eimm) {
3598           return s390_emit_AFI(p, r1, i2);
3599        }
3600        /* Load 32 bit immediate to R0 then add */
3601        p = s390_emit_load_32imm(p, R0, i2);
3602        return s390_emit_AR(p, r1, R0);
3603     }

3607     static UChar *

3610        if (s390_host_has_eimm) {
3611           return s390_emit_SLFI(p, r1, i2);
3612        }
3613     
3614        /* Load 32 bit immediate to R0 then subtract */
3615        p = s390_emit_load_32imm(p, R0, i2);
3616        return s390_emit_SR(p, r1, R0);
3617     }

3620     static UChar *
3621     s390_emit_LTw(UChar *p, UChar r1, UChar x2, UChar b2, UShort dl, UChar dh)
3622     {
3623        if (s390_host_has_eimm) {
3624           return s390_emit_LT(p, r1, x2, b2, dl, dh);
3625        }
3626        /* Load 32 bit from memory to R0 then compare */
3627        if (dh == 0) {
3628           p = s390_emit_L(p, R0, x2, b2, dl);
3629        } else {
3630           p = s390_emit_LY(p, R0, x2, b2, dl, dh);
3631        }
3632        return s390_emit_LTR(p, r1, R0);
3633     }

3640           return s390_emit_LTG(p, r1, x2, b2, dl, dh);
3641        }
3642        /* Load 64 bit from memory to R0 then compare */
3643        p = s390_emit_LG(p, R0, x2, b2, dl, dh);
3644        return s390_emit_LTGR(p, r1, R0);

3681     {

3683

3685        insn->size = size;
3686        insn->variant.load.src  = src;
3687        insn->variant.load.dst  = dst;
3688     
3689        vassert(size == 1 || size == 2 || size == 4 || size == 8);
3690     
3691        return insn;
3692     }

3774     s390_insn_mul(UChar size, HReg dst_hi, HReg dst_lo, s390_opnd_RMI op2,
3775                   Bool signed_multiply)

3783        insn->size = size;
