4131     /*---------------------------------------------------------------*/
4132     /*--- Debug print                                             ---*/
4133     /*---------------------------------------------------------------*/
4134     
4135     static const HChar *
4136     s390_cc_as_string(s390_cc_t cc)
4137     {
4138        switch (cc) {
4139        case S390_CC_NEVER:  return "never";
4140        case S390_CC_OVFL:   return "overflow";
4141        case S390_CC_H:      return "greater than";     /* A > B ; high */
4142        case S390_CC_NLE:    return "not low or equal";
4143        case S390_CC_L:      return "less than";        /* A < B ; low */
4144        case S390_CC_NHE:    return "not high or equal";
4145        case S390_CC_LH:     return "low or high";
4146        case S390_CC_NE:     return "not equal";        /* A != B ; not zero */
4147        case S390_CC_E:      return "equal";            /* A == B ; zero */
4148        case S390_CC_NLH:    return "not low or high";
4149        case S390_CC_HE:     return "greater or equal"; /* A >= B ; high or equal*/
4150        case S390_CC_NL:     return "not low";          /* not low */
4151        case S390_CC_LE:     return "less or equal";    /* A <= B ; low or equal */
4152        case S390_CC_NH:     return "not high";
4153        case S390_CC_NO:     return "not overflow";
4154        case S390_CC_ALWAYS: return "always";
4155        default:
4156           vpanic("s390_cc_as_string");
4157        }
4158     }
4159     
4160     
4161     /* Helper function for writing out a V insn */
4162     static void
4163     s390_sprintf(HChar *buf, HChar *fmt, ...)
4164     {
4165        HChar *p;
4166        ULong value;
4167        va_list args;
4168        va_start(args, fmt);
4169     
4170        p = buf;
4171        for ( ; *fmt; ++fmt) {
4172           Int c = *fmt;
4173     
4174           if (c != '%') {
4175              *p++ = c;
4176              continue;
4177           }
4178     
4179           c = *++fmt;  /* next char */
4180           switch (c) {
4181           case '%':
4182              *p++ = c;   /* %% */
4183              continue;
4184     
4185           case 's':     /* %s */
4186              p += vex_sprintf(p, "%s", va_arg(args, HChar *));
4187              continue;
4188     
4189           case 'M':     /* %M = mnemonic */
4190              p += vex_sprintf(p, "%-8s", va_arg(args, HChar *));
4191              continue;
4192     
4193           case 'R':     /* %R = register */
4194              p += vex_sprintf(p, "%s", s390_hreg_as_string(va_arg(args, HReg)));
4195              continue;
4196     
4197           case 'A':     /* %A = amode */
4198              p += vex_sprintf(p, "%s",
4199                               s390_amode_as_string(va_arg(args, s390_amode *)));
4200              continue;
4201     
4202           case 'C':     /* %C = condition code */
4203              p += vex_sprintf(p, "%s", s390_cc_as_string(va_arg(args, s390_cc_t)));
4204              continue;
4205     
4206           case 'L': {   /* %L = argument list in helper call*/
4207              UInt i, num_args;
4208     
4209              num_args = va_arg(args, UInt);
4210     
4211              for (i = 0; i < num_args; ++i) {
4212                 if (i != 0) p += vex_sprintf(p, ", ");
4213                 p += vex_sprintf(p, "r%d", s390_gprno_from_arg_index(i));
4214              }
4215              continue;
4216           }
4217     
4218           case 'O': {   /* %O = RMI operand */
4219              s390_opnd_RMI *op = va_arg(args, s390_opnd_RMI *);
4220     
4221              switch (op->tag) {
4222              case S390_OPND_REG:
4223                 p += vex_sprintf(p, "%s", s390_hreg_as_string(op->variant.reg));
4224                 continue;
4225     
4226              case S390_OPND_AMODE:
4227                 p += vex_sprintf(p, "%s", s390_amode_as_string(op->variant.am));
4228                 continue;
4229     
4230              case S390_OPND_IMMEDIATE:
4231                 value = op->variant.imm;
4232                 goto print_value;
4233     
4234              default:
4235                 goto fail;
4236              }
4237           }
4238     
4239           case 'I':     /* %I = immediate value */
4240              value = va_arg(args, ULong);
4241              goto print_value;
4242     
4243           print_value:
4244              if ((Long)value < 0)
4245                 p += vex_sprintf(p, "%lld", (Long)value);
4246              else if (value < 100)
4247                 p += vex_sprintf(p, "%llu", value);
4248              else
4249                 p += vex_sprintf(p, "0x%llx", value);
4250              continue;
4251     
4252           default:
4253              goto fail;
4254           }
4255        }
4256        *p = '\0';
4257        va_end(args);
4258     
4259        return;
4260     
4261      fail: vpanic("s390_printf");
4262     }
4263     
4264     
4265     /* Decompile the given insn into a static buffer and return it */
4266     const HChar *
4267     s390_insn_as_string(const s390_insn *insn)
4268     {
4269        static HChar buf[300];
4270        const HChar *op;
4271        HChar *p;
4272     
4273        buf[0] = '\0';
4274     
4275        switch (insn->tag) {
4276        case S390_INSN_LOAD:
4277           s390_sprintf(buf, "%M %R,%A", "v-load", insn->variant.load.dst,
4278                        insn->variant.load.src);
4279           break;
4280     
4281        case S390_INSN_STORE:
4282           s390_sprintf(buf, "%M %R,%A", "v-store", insn->variant.store.src,
4283                        insn->variant.store.dst);
4284           break;
4285     
4286        case S390_INSN_MOVE:
4287           s390_sprintf(buf, "%M %R,%R", "v-move", insn->variant.move.dst,
4288                        insn->variant.move.src);
4289           break;
4290     
4291        case S390_INSN_COND_MOVE:
4292           s390_sprintf(buf, "%M if (%C) %R,%O", "v-move",
4293                        insn->variant.cond_move.cond, insn->variant.cond_move.dst,
4294                        &insn->variant.cond_move.src);
4295           break;
4296     
4297        case S390_INSN_LOAD_IMMEDIATE:
4298           s390_sprintf(buf, "%M %R,%I", "v-loadi", insn->variant.load_immediate.dst,
4299                        insn->variant.load_immediate.value);
4300           break;
4301     
4302        case S390_INSN_ALU:
4303           switch (insn->variant.alu.tag) {
4304           case S390_ALU_ADD:  op = "v-add";  break;
4305           case S390_ALU_SUB:  op = "v-sub";  break;
4306           case S390_ALU_MUL:  op = "v-mul";  break;
4307           case S390_ALU_AND:  op = "v-and";  break;
4308           case S390_ALU_OR:   op = "v-or";   break;
4309           case S390_ALU_XOR:  op = "v-xor";  break;
4310           case S390_ALU_LSH:  op = "v-lsh";  break;
4311           case S390_ALU_RSH:  op = "v-rsh";  break;
4312           case S390_ALU_RSHA: op = "v-rsha"; break;
4313           default: goto fail;
4314           }
4315           s390_sprintf(buf, "%M %R,%R,%O", op, insn->variant.alu.dst,
4316                        insn->variant.alu.dst   /* op1 same as dst */,
4317                        &insn->variant.alu.op2);
4318           break;
4319     
4320        case S390_INSN_MUL:
4321           if (insn->variant.mul.signed_multiply) {
4322              op = "v-muls";
4323           } else {
4324              op = "v-mulu";
4325           }
4326           s390_sprintf(buf, "%M %R,%O", op, insn->variant.mul.dst_hi,
4327                        &insn->variant.mul.op2);
4328           break;
4329     
4330        case S390_INSN_DIV:
4331           if (insn->variant.div.signed_divide) {
4332              op = "v-divs";
4333           } else {
4334              op = "v-divu";
4335           }
4336           s390_sprintf(buf, "%M %R,%O", op, insn->variant.div.op1_hi,
4337                        &insn->variant.div.op2);
4338           break;
4339     
4340        case S390_INSN_DIVS:
4341           s390_sprintf(buf, "%M %R,%O", "v-divsi", insn->variant.divs.op1,
4342                        &insn->variant.divs.op2);
4343           break;
4344     
4345        case S390_INSN_CLZ:
4346           s390_sprintf(buf, "%M %R,%O", "v-clz", insn->variant.clz.num_bits,
4347                        &insn->variant.clz.src);
4348           break;
4349     
4350        case S390_INSN_UNOP:
4351           switch (insn->variant.unop.tag) {
4352           case S390_ZERO_EXTEND_8:
4353           case S390_ZERO_EXTEND_16:
4354           case S390_ZERO_EXTEND_32:
4355              op = "v-zerox";
4356              break;
4357     
4358           case S390_SIGN_EXTEND_8:
4359           case S390_SIGN_EXTEND_16:
4360           case S390_SIGN_EXTEND_32:
4361              op = "v-signx";
4362              break;
4363     
4364           case S390_NEGATE:
4365              op = "v-neg";
4366              break;
4367     
4368           default:
4369              goto fail;
4370           }
4371           s390_sprintf(buf, "%M %R,%O", op, insn->variant.unop.dst,
4372                        &insn->variant.unop.src);
4373           break;
4374     
4375        case S390_INSN_TEST:
4376           s390_sprintf(buf, "%M %O", "v-test", &insn->variant.test.src);
4377           break;
4378     
4379        case S390_INSN_CC2BOOL:
4380           s390_sprintf(buf, "%M %R,%C", "v-cc2b", insn->variant.cc2bool.dst,
4381                        insn->variant.cc2bool.cond);
4382           break;
4383     
4384        case S390_INSN_CAS:
4385           s390_sprintf(buf, "%M %R,%A,%R,%R", "v-cas", insn->variant.cas.op1,
4386                        insn->variant.cas.op2, insn->variant.cas.op3,
4387                        insn->variant.cas.old_mem);
4388           break;
4389     
4390        case S390_INSN_COMPARE:
4391           if (insn->variant.compare.signed_comparison) {
4392              op = "v-cmps";
4393           } else {
4394              op = "v-cmpu";
4395           }
4396           s390_sprintf(buf, "%M %R,%O", op, insn->variant.compare.src1,
4397                        &insn->variant.compare.src2);
4398           break;
4399     
4400        case S390_INSN_BRANCH:
4401           switch (insn->variant.branch.kind) {
4402           case Ijk_ClientReq:   op = "clientreq"; break;
4403           case Ijk_Sys_syscall: op = "syscall";   break;
4404           case Ijk_Yield:       op = "yield";     break;
4405           case Ijk_EmWarn:      op = "emwarn";    break;
4406           case Ijk_EmFail:      op = "emfail";    break;
4407           case Ijk_MapFail:     op = "mapfail";   break;
4408           case Ijk_NoDecode:    op = "nodecode";  break;
4409           case Ijk_TInval:      op = "tinval";    break;
4410           case Ijk_NoRedir:     op = "noredir";   break;
4411           case Ijk_SigTRAP:     op = "sigtrap";   break;
4412           case Ijk_Boring:      op = "goto";      break;
4413           case Ijk_Call:        op = "call";      break;
4414           case Ijk_Ret:         op = "return";    break;
4415           default:
4416              goto fail;
4417           }
4418           s390_sprintf(buf, "if (%C) %s %O", insn->variant.branch.cond, op,
4419                        &insn->variant.branch.dst);
4420           break;
4421     
4422        case S390_INSN_HELPER_CALL: {
4423     
4424           if (insn->variant.helper_call.cond != S390_CC_ALWAYS) {
4425              s390_sprintf(buf, "%M if (%C) %s{%I}(%L)", "v-call",
4426                           insn->variant.helper_call.cond,
4427                           insn->variant.helper_call.name,
4428                           insn->variant.helper_call.target,
4429                           insn->variant.helper_call.num_args);
4430           } else {
4431              s390_sprintf(buf, "%M %s{%I}(%L)", "v-call",
4432                           insn->variant.helper_call.name,
4433                           insn->variant.helper_call.target,
4434                           insn->variant.helper_call.num_args);
4435           }
4436           break;
4437        }
4438     
4439        case S390_INSN_BFP_TRIOP:
4440           switch (insn->variant.bfp_triop.tag) {
4441           case S390_BFP_MADD:  op = "v-fmadd";  break;
4442           case S390_BFP_MSUB:  op = "v-fmsub";  break;
4443           default: goto fail;
4444           }
4445           s390_sprintf(buf, "%M %R,%R,%R,%R", op, insn->variant.bfp_triop.dst,
4446                        insn->variant.bfp_triop.dst  /* op1 same as dst */,
4447                        insn->variant.bfp_triop.op2, insn->variant.bfp_triop.op3);
4448           break;
4449     
4450        case S390_INSN_BFP_BINOP:
4451           switch (insn->variant.bfp_binop.tag) {
4452           case S390_BFP_ADD:      op = "v-fadd";  break;
4453           case S390_BFP_SUB:      op = "v-fsub";  break;
4454           case S390_BFP_MUL:      op = "v-fmul";  break;
4455           case S390_BFP_DIV:      op = "v-fdiv";  break;
4456           default: goto fail;
4457           }
4458           s390_sprintf(buf, "%M %R,%R,%R", op, insn->variant.bfp_binop.dst,
4459                        insn->variant.bfp_binop.dst  /* op1 same as dst */,
4460                        insn->variant.bfp_binop.op2);
4461           break;
4462     
4463        case S390_INSN_BFP_COMPARE:
4464           s390_sprintf(buf, "%M %R,%R,%R", "v-fcmp", insn->variant.bfp_compare.dst,
4465                        insn->variant.bfp_compare.op1, insn->variant.bfp_compare.op2);
4466           break;
4467     
4468        case S390_INSN_BFP_UNOP:
4469           switch (insn->variant.bfp_unop.tag) {
4470           case S390_BFP_ABS:         op = "v-fabs";  break;
4471           case S390_BFP_NABS:        op = "v-fnabs"; break;
4472           case S390_BFP_NEG:         op = "v-fneg";  break;
4473           case S390_BFP_SQRT:        op = "v-fsqrt"; break;
4474           case S390_BFP_I32_TO_F32:
4475           case S390_BFP_I32_TO_F64:
4476           case S390_BFP_I32_TO_F128:
4477           case S390_BFP_I64_TO_F32:
4478           case S390_BFP_I64_TO_F64:
4479           case S390_BFP_I64_TO_F128: op = "v-i2f"; break;
4480           case S390_BFP_F32_TO_I32:
4481           case S390_BFP_F32_TO_I64:
4482           case S390_BFP_F64_TO_I32:
4483           case S390_BFP_F64_TO_I64:
4484           case S390_BFP_F128_TO_I32:
4485           case S390_BFP_F128_TO_I64: op = "v-f2i"; break;
4486           case S390_BFP_F32_TO_F64:
4487           case S390_BFP_F32_TO_F128:
4488           case S390_BFP_F64_TO_F32:
4489           case S390_BFP_F64_TO_F128:
4490           case S390_BFP_F128_TO_F32:
4491           case S390_BFP_F128_TO_F64: op = "v-f2f"; break;
4492           default: goto fail;
4493           }
4494           s390_sprintf(buf, "%M %R,%R", op, insn->variant.bfp_unop.dst,
4495                        insn->variant.bfp_unop.op);
4496           break;
4497     
4498        case S390_INSN_BFP128_BINOP:
4499           switch (insn->variant.bfp128_binop.tag) {
4500           case S390_BFP_ADD:      op = "v-fadd";  break;
4501           case S390_BFP_SUB:      op = "v-fsub";  break;
4502           case S390_BFP_MUL:      op = "v-fmul";  break;
4503           case S390_BFP_DIV:      op = "v-fdiv";  break;
4504           default: goto fail;
4505           }
4506           /* Only write the register that identifies the register pair */
4507           s390_sprintf(buf, "%M %R,%R,%R", op, insn->variant.bfp128_binop.dst_hi,
4508                        insn->variant.bfp128_binop.dst_hi  /* op1 same as dst */,
4509                        insn->variant.bfp128_binop.op2_hi);
4510           break;
4511     
4512        case S390_INSN_BFP128_COMPARE:
4513           /* Only write the register that identifies the register pair */
4514           s390_sprintf(buf, "%M %R,%R,%R", "v-fcmp", insn->variant.bfp128_compare.dst,
4515                        insn->variant.bfp128_compare.op1_hi,
4516                        insn->variant.bfp128_compare.op2_hi);
4517           break;
4518     
4519        case S390_INSN_BFP128_UNOP:
4520        case S390_INSN_BFP128_CONVERT_TO:
4521        case S390_INSN_BFP128_CONVERT_FROM:
4522           switch (insn->variant.bfp128_unop.tag) {
4523           case S390_BFP_ABS:         op = "v-fabs";  break;
4524           case S390_BFP_NABS:        op = "v-fnabs"; break;
4525           case S390_BFP_NEG:         op = "v-fneg";  break;
4526           case S390_BFP_SQRT:        op = "v-fsqrt"; break;
4527           case S390_BFP_I32_TO_F128:
4528           case S390_BFP_I64_TO_F128: op = "v-i2f";   break;
4529           case S390_BFP_F128_TO_I32:
4530           case S390_BFP_F128_TO_I64: op = "v-f2i";   break;
4531           case S390_BFP_F32_TO_F128:
4532           case S390_BFP_F64_TO_F128:
4533           case S390_BFP_F128_TO_F32:
4534           case S390_BFP_F128_TO_F64: op = "v-f2f";   break;
4535           default: goto fail;
4536           }
4537           /* Only write the register that identifies the register pair */
4538           s390_sprintf(buf, "%M %R,%R", op, insn->variant.bfp128_unop.dst_hi,
4539                        insn->variant.bfp128_unop.op_hi);
4540           break;
4541     
4542        default: goto fail;
4543        }
4544     
4545        /* Write out how many bytes are involved in the operation */
4546     
4547        {
4548           UInt len, i;
4549     
4550           for (p = buf; *p; ++p)
4551              continue;
4552     
4553           len = p - buf;
4554     
4555           if (len < 32) {
4556              for (i = len; i < 32; ++i)
4557                 p += vex_sprintf(p, " ");
4558           } else {
4559              p += vex_sprintf(p, "\t");
4560           }
4561        }
4562     
4563        /* Special cases first */
4564        switch (insn->tag) {
4565        case S390_INSN_UNOP:
4566           switch (insn->variant.unop.tag) {
4567           case S390_SIGN_EXTEND_8:
4568           case S390_ZERO_EXTEND_8:  p += vex_sprintf(p, "1 -> "); goto common;
4569           case S390_SIGN_EXTEND_16:
4570           case S390_ZERO_EXTEND_16: p += vex_sprintf(p, "2 -> "); goto common;
4571           case S390_SIGN_EXTEND_32:
4572           case S390_ZERO_EXTEND_32: p += vex_sprintf(p, "4 -> "); goto common;
4573           default:
4574              goto common;
4575           }
4576     
4577        case S390_INSN_BFP_UNOP:
4578           switch (insn->variant.bfp_unop.tag) {
4579           case S390_BFP_I32_TO_F32:
4580           case S390_BFP_I32_TO_F64:
4581           case S390_BFP_I32_TO_F128:
4582           case S390_BFP_F32_TO_I32:
4583           case S390_BFP_F32_TO_I64:
4584           case S390_BFP_F32_TO_F64:
4585           case S390_BFP_F32_TO_F128: p += vex_sprintf(p, "4 -> "); goto common;
4586           case S390_BFP_I64_TO_F32:
4587           case S390_BFP_I64_TO_F64:
4588           case S390_BFP_I64_TO_F128:
4589           case S390_BFP_F64_TO_I32:
4590           case S390_BFP_F64_TO_I64:
4591           case S390_BFP_F64_TO_F32:
4592           case S390_BFP_F64_TO_F128: p += vex_sprintf(p, "8 -> "); goto common;
4593           case S390_BFP_F128_TO_I32:
4594           case S390_BFP_F128_TO_I64:
4595           case S390_BFP_F128_TO_F32:
4596           case S390_BFP_F128_TO_F64: p += vex_sprintf(p, "16 -> "); goto common;
4597           default:
4598              goto common;
4599           }
4600     
4601        case S390_INSN_BFP128_UNOP:
4602        case S390_INSN_BFP128_CONVERT_TO:
4603        case S390_INSN_BFP128_CONVERT_FROM:
4604           switch (insn->variant.bfp128_unop.tag) {
4605           case S390_BFP_I32_TO_F128:
4606           case S390_BFP_F32_TO_F128: p += vex_sprintf(p, "4 -> "); goto common;
4607           case S390_BFP_I64_TO_F128:
4608           case S390_BFP_F64_TO_F128: p += vex_sprintf(p, "8 -> "); goto common;
4609           case S390_BFP_F128_TO_I32:
4610           case S390_BFP_F128_TO_I64:
4611           case S390_BFP_F128_TO_F32:
4612           case S390_BFP_F128_TO_F64: p += vex_sprintf(p, "16 -> "); goto common;
4613           default:
4614              goto common;
4615           }
4616     
4617        default:
4618           goto common;
4619        }
4620     
4621        /* Common case */
4622      common:
4623        vex_sprintf(p, "%u bytes", (UInt)insn->size);
4624     
4625        return buf;
4626     
4627      fail: vpanic("s390_insn_as_string");
4628     }
4629     
4630     
4631     
4632     /* Load NUM bytes from memory into register REG using addressing mode AM. */
4633     static UChar *
4634     s390_emit_load_mem(UChar *p, UInt num, UChar reg, const s390_amode *am)
4635     {
4636        UInt b = hregNumber(am->b);
4637        UInt x = hregNumber(am->x);  /* 0 for B12 and B20 */
4638        UInt d = am->d;
4639     
4640        switch (am->tag) {
4641        case S390_AMODE_B12:
4642        case S390_AMODE_BX12:
4643           switch (num) {
4644           case 1: return s390_emit_IC(p, reg, x, b, d);
4645           case 2: return s390_emit_LH(p, reg, x, b, d);
4646           case 4: return s390_emit_L(p, reg, x, b, d);
4647           case 8: return s390_emit_LG(p, reg, x, b, DISP20(d));
4648           default: goto fail;
4649           }
4650           break;
4651     
4652        case S390_AMODE_B20:
4653        case S390_AMODE_BX20:
4654           switch (num) {
4655           case 1: return s390_emit_ICY(p, reg, x, b, DISP20(d));
4656           case 2: return s390_emit_LHY(p, reg, x, b, DISP20(d));
4657           case 4: return s390_emit_LY(p, reg, x, b, DISP20(d));
4658           case 8: return s390_emit_LG(p, reg, x, b, DISP20(d));
4659           default: goto fail;
4660           }
4661           break;
4662     
4663        default: goto fail;
4664        }
4665     
4666      fail:
4667        vpanic("s390_emit_load_mem");
4668     }
4669     
4670     
4671     /* Load condition code into register REG */
4672     static UChar *
4673     s390_emit_load_cc(UChar *p, UChar reg)
4674     {
4675        p = s390_emit_LGHI(p, reg, 0);  /* Clear out, cc not affected */
4676        p = s390_emit_IPM(p, reg, reg);
4677        /* Shift 28 bits to the right --> [0,1,2,3] */
4678        return s390_emit_SRL(p, reg, 0, 28); /* REG = cc */
4679     }
4680     
4681     
4682     /*---------------------------------------------------------------*/
4683     /*--- Code generation                                         ---*/
4684     /*---------------------------------------------------------------*/
4685     
4686     /* Do not load more bytes than requested. */
4687     static UChar *
4688     s390_insn_load_emit(UChar *buf, const s390_insn *insn)
4689     {
4690        UInt r, x, b, d;
4691        const s390_amode *src;
4692     
4693        src = insn->variant.load.src;
4694     
4695        r = hregNumber(insn->variant.load.dst);
4696     
4697        if (hregClass(insn->variant.load.dst) == HRcFlt64) {
4698           b = hregNumber(src->b);
4699           x = hregNumber(src->x);  /* 0 for B12 and B20 */
4700           d = src->d;
4701     
4702           switch (insn->size) {
4703     
4704           case 4:
4705              switch (src->tag) {
4706              case S390_AMODE_B12:
4707              case S390_AMODE_BX12:
4708                 return s390_emit_LE(buf, r, x, b, d);
4709     
4710              case S390_AMODE_B20:
4711              case S390_AMODE_BX20:
4712                 return s390_emit_LEY(buf, r, x, b, DISP20(d));
4713              }
4714              break;
4715     
4716           case 8:
4717              switch (src->tag) {
4718              case S390_AMODE_B12:
4719              case S390_AMODE_BX12:
4720                 return s390_emit_LD(buf, r, x, b, d);
4721     
4722              case S390_AMODE_B20:
4723              case S390_AMODE_BX20:
4724                 return s390_emit_LDY(buf, r, x, b, DISP20(d));
4725              }
4726              break;
4727           }
4728           vpanic("s390_insn_load_emit");
4729        }
4730     
4731        /* Integer stuff */
4732        return s390_emit_load_mem(buf, insn->size, r, src);
4733     }
4734     
4735     
4736     static UChar *
4737     s390_insn_store_emit(UChar *buf, const s390_insn *insn)
4738     {
4739        UInt r, x, b, d;
4740        const s390_amode *dst;
4741     
4742        dst = insn->variant.store.dst;
4743     
4744        r = hregNumber(insn->variant.store.src);
4745        b = hregNumber(dst->b);
4746        x = hregNumber(dst->x);  /* 0 for B12 and B20 */
4747        d = dst->d;
4748     
4749        if (hregClass(insn->variant.store.src) == HRcFlt64) {
4750           switch (insn->size) {
4751     
4752           case 4:
4753              switch (dst->tag) {
4754              case S390_AMODE_B12:
4755              case S390_AMODE_BX12:
4756                 return s390_emit_STE(buf, r, x, b, d);
4757     
4758              case S390_AMODE_B20:
4759              case S390_AMODE_BX20:
4760                 return s390_emit_STEY(buf, r, x, b, DISP20(d));
4761              }
4762              break;
4763     
4764           case 8:
4765              switch (dst->tag) {
4766              case S390_AMODE_B12:
4767              case S390_AMODE_BX12:
4768                 return s390_emit_STD(buf, r, x, b, d);
4769     
4770              case S390_AMODE_B20:
4771              case S390_AMODE_BX20:
4772                 return s390_emit_STDY(buf, r, x, b, DISP20(d));
4773              }
4774              break;
4775           }
4776           vpanic("s390_insn_store_emit");
4777        }
4778     
4779        /* Integer stuff */
4780        switch (insn->size) {
4781        case 1:
4782           switch (dst->tag) {
4783           case S390_AMODE_B12:
4784           case S390_AMODE_BX12:
4785              return s390_emit_STC(buf, r, x, b, d);
4786     
4787           case S390_AMODE_B20:
4788           case S390_AMODE_BX20:
4789              return s390_emit_STCY(buf, r, x, b, DISP20(d));
4790           }
4791           break;
4792     
4793        case 2:
4794           switch (dst->tag) {
4795           case S390_AMODE_B12:
4796           case S390_AMODE_BX12:
4797              return s390_emit_STH(buf, r, x, b, d);
4798     
4799           case S390_AMODE_B20:
4800           case S390_AMODE_BX20:
4801              return s390_emit_STHY(buf, r, x, b, DISP20(d));
4802           }
4803           break;
4804     
4805        case 4:
4806           switch (dst->tag) {
4807           case S390_AMODE_B12:
4808           case S390_AMODE_BX12:
4809              return s390_emit_ST(buf, r, x, b, d);
4810     
4811           case S390_AMODE_B20:
4812           case S390_AMODE_BX20:
4813              return s390_emit_STY(buf, r, x, b, DISP20(d));
4814           }
4815           break;
4816     
4817        case 8:
4818           return s390_emit_STG(buf, r, x, b, DISP20(d));
4819     
4820        default:
4821           break;
4822        }
4823     
4824        vpanic("s390_insn_store_emit");
4825     }
4826     
4827     
4828     static UChar *
4829     s390_insn_move_emit(UChar *buf, const s390_insn *insn)
4830     {
4831        UInt dst, src;
4832        HRegClass dst_class, src_class;
4833     
4834        dst = hregNumber(insn->variant.move.dst);
4835        src = hregNumber(insn->variant.move.src);
4836     
4837        dst_class = hregClass(insn->variant.move.dst);
4838        src_class = hregClass(insn->variant.move.src);
4839     
4840        if (dst_class == src_class) {
4841           if (dst_class == HRcInt64)
4842              return s390_emit_LGR(buf, dst, src);
4843           if (dst_class == HRcFlt64)
4844              return s390_emit_LDR(buf, dst, src);
4845        } else {
4846           if (dst_class == HRcFlt64 && src_class == HRcInt64)
4847              return s390_emit_LDGR(buf, dst, src);
4848           if (dst_class == HRcInt64 && src_class == HRcFlt64)
4849              return s390_emit_LGDR(buf, dst, src);
4850           /* A move between floating point registers and general purpose
4851              registers of different size should never occur and indicates
4852              an error elsewhere. */
4853        }
4854     
4855        vpanic("s390_insn_move_emit");
4856     }
4857     
4858     
4859     static UChar *
4860     s390_insn_load_immediate_emit(UChar *buf, const s390_insn *insn)
4861     {
4862        UInt  r;
4863        ULong value = insn->variant.load_immediate.value;
4864     
4865        r = hregNumber(insn->variant.load_immediate.dst);
4866     
4867        if (hregClass(insn->variant.load_immediate.dst) == HRcFlt64) {
4868           vassert(value == 0);
4869           switch (insn->size) {
4870           case 4: return s390_emit_LZER(buf, r, value);
4871           case 8: return s390_emit_LZDR(buf, r, value);
4872           }
4873           vpanic("s390_insn_load_immediate_emit");
4874        }
4875     
4876        switch (insn->size) {
4877        case 1:
4878        case 2:
4879           /* Load the immediate values as a 4 byte value. That does not hurt as
4880              those extra bytes will not be looked at. Fall through .... */
4881        case 4:
4882           return s390_emit_load_32imm(buf, r, value);
4883     
4884        case 8:
4885           return s390_emit_load_64imm(buf, r, value);
4886        }
4887     
4888        vpanic("s390_insn_load_immediate_emit");
4889     }
4890     
4891     
4892     /* There is no easy way to do ALU operations on 1-byte or 2-byte operands.
4893        So we simply perform a 4-byte operation. Doing so uses possibly undefined
4894        bits and produces an undefined result in those extra bit positions. But
4895        upstream does not look at those positions, so this is OK. */
4896     static UChar *
4897     s390_insn_alu_emit(UChar *buf, const s390_insn *insn)
4898     {
4899        s390_opnd_RMI op2;
4900        UInt dst;
4901     
4902        dst = hregNumber(insn->variant.alu.dst);
4903        op2 = insn->variant.alu.op2;
4904     
4905        /* Second operand is in a register */
4906        if (op2.tag == S390_OPND_REG) {
4907           UInt r2 = hregNumber(op2.variant.reg);
4908     
4909           switch (insn->size) {
4910           case 1:
4911           case 2:
4912           case 4:
4913              switch (insn->variant.alu.tag) {
4914              case S390_ALU_ADD:  return s390_emit_AR(buf, dst, r2);
4915              case S390_ALU_SUB:  return s390_emit_SR(buf, dst, r2);
4916              case S390_ALU_MUL:  return s390_emit_MSR(buf, dst, r2);
4917              case S390_ALU_AND:  return s390_emit_NR(buf, dst, r2);
4918              case S390_ALU_OR:   return s390_emit_OR(buf, dst, r2);
4919              case S390_ALU_XOR:  return s390_emit_XR(buf, dst, r2);
4920              case S390_ALU_LSH:  return s390_emit_SLL(buf, dst, r2, 0);
4921              case S390_ALU_RSH:  return s390_emit_SRL(buf, dst, r2, 0);
4922              case S390_ALU_RSHA: return s390_emit_SRA(buf, dst, r2, 0);
4923              }
4924              goto fail;
4925     
4926           case 8:
4927              switch (insn->variant.alu.tag) {
4928              case S390_ALU_ADD:  return s390_emit_AGR(buf, dst, r2);
4929              case S390_ALU_SUB:  return s390_emit_SGR(buf, dst, r2);
4930              case S390_ALU_MUL:  return s390_emit_MSGR(buf, dst, r2);
4931              case S390_ALU_AND:  return s390_emit_NGR(buf, dst, r2);
4932              case S390_ALU_OR:   return s390_emit_OGR(buf, dst, r2);
4933              case S390_ALU_XOR:  return s390_emit_XGR(buf, dst, r2);
4934              case S390_ALU_LSH:  return s390_emit_SLLG(buf, dst, dst, r2, DISP20(0));
4935              case S390_ALU_RSH:  return s390_emit_SRLG(buf, dst, dst, r2, DISP20(0));
4936              case S390_ALU_RSHA: return s390_emit_SRAG(buf, dst, dst, r2, DISP20(0));
4937              }
4938              goto fail;
4939           }
4940           goto fail;
4941        }
4942     
4943        /* 2nd operand is in memory */
4944        if (op2.tag == S390_OPND_AMODE) {
4945           UInt b, x, d;
4946           const s390_amode *src = op2.variant.am;
4947     
4948           b = hregNumber(src->b);
4949           x = hregNumber(src->x);  /* 0 for B12 and B20 */
4950           d = src->d;
4951     
4952           /* Shift operands are special here as there are no opcodes that
4953              allow a memory operand. So we first load the 2nd operand to R0. */
4954           if (insn->variant.alu.tag == S390_ALU_LSH ||
4955               insn->variant.alu.tag == S390_ALU_RSH ||
4956               insn->variant.alu.tag == S390_ALU_RSHA) {
4957     
4958              buf = s390_emit_load_mem(buf, insn->size, R0, src);
4959     
4960              if (insn->size == 8) {
4961                 if (insn->variant.alu.tag == S390_ALU_LSH)
4962                    return s390_emit_SLLG(buf, dst, dst, R0, DISP20(0));
4963                 if (insn->variant.alu.tag == S390_ALU_RSH)
4964                    return s390_emit_SRLG(buf, dst, dst, R0, DISP20(0));
4965                 if (insn->variant.alu.tag == S390_ALU_RSHA)
4966                    return s390_emit_SRAG(buf, dst, dst, R0, DISP20(0));
4967              } else {
4968                 if (insn->variant.alu.tag == S390_ALU_LSH)
4969                    return s390_emit_SLL(buf, dst, R0, 0);
4970                 if (insn->variant.alu.tag == S390_ALU_RSH)
4971                    return s390_emit_SRL(buf, dst, R0, 0);
4972                 if (insn->variant.alu.tag == S390_ALU_RSHA)
4973                    return s390_emit_SRA(buf, dst, R0, 0);
4974              }
4975           }
4976     
4977           switch (insn->size) {
4978           case 1:
4979              /* Move the byte from memory into scratch register r0 */
4980              buf = s390_emit_load_mem(buf, 1, R0, src);
4981     
4982              switch (insn->variant.alu.tag) {
4983              case S390_ALU_ADD: return s390_emit_AR(buf, dst, R0);
4984              case S390_ALU_SUB: return s390_emit_SR(buf, dst, R0);
4985              case S390_ALU_MUL: return s390_emit_MSR(buf, dst, R0);
4986              case S390_ALU_AND: return s390_emit_NR(buf, dst, R0);
4987              case S390_ALU_OR:  return s390_emit_OR(buf, dst, R0);
4988              case S390_ALU_XOR: return s390_emit_XR(buf, dst, R0);
4989              case S390_ALU_LSH:
4990              case S390_ALU_RSH:
4991              case S390_ALU_RSHA: ; /* avoid GCC warning */
4992              }
4993              goto fail;
4994     
4995           case 2:
4996              switch (src->tag) {
4997              case S390_AMODE_B12:
4998              case S390_AMODE_BX12:
4999                 switch (insn->variant.alu.tag) {
5000                 case S390_ALU_ADD:
5001                    return s390_emit_AH(buf, dst, x, b, d);
5002     
5003                 case S390_ALU_SUB:
5004                    return s390_emit_SH(buf, dst, x, b, d);
5005     
5006                 case S390_ALU_MUL:
5007                    return s390_emit_MH(buf, dst, x, b, d);
5008     
5009                    /* For bitwise operations: Move two bytes from memory into scratch
5010                       register r0; then perform operation */
5011                 case S390_ALU_AND:
5012                    buf = s390_emit_LH(buf, R0, x, b, d);
5013                    return s390_emit_NR(buf, dst, R0);
5014     
5015                 case S390_ALU_OR:
5016                    buf = s390_emit_LH(buf, R0, x, b, d);
5017                    return s390_emit_OR(buf, dst, R0);
5018     
5019                 case S390_ALU_XOR:
5020                    buf = s390_emit_LH(buf, R0, x, b, d);
5021                    return s390_emit_XR(buf, dst, R0);
5022     
5023                 case S390_ALU_LSH:
5024                 case S390_ALU_RSH:
5025                 case S390_ALU_RSHA: ; /* avoid GCC warning */
5026                 }
5027                 goto fail;
5028     
5029              case S390_AMODE_B20:
5030              case S390_AMODE_BX20:
5031                 switch (insn->variant.alu.tag) {
5032                 case S390_ALU_ADD:
5033                    return s390_emit_AHY(buf, dst, x, b, DISP20(d));
5034     
5035                 case S390_ALU_SUB:
5036                    return s390_emit_SHY(buf, dst, x, b, DISP20(d));
5037     
5038                 case S390_ALU_MUL:
5039                    return s390_emit_MHYw(buf, dst, x, b, DISP20(d));
5040     
5041                    /* For bitwise operations: Move two bytes from memory into scratch
5042                       register r0; then perform operation */
5043                 case S390_ALU_AND:
5044                    buf = s390_emit_LHY(buf, R0, x, b, DISP20(d));
5045                    return s390_emit_NR(buf, dst, R0);
5046     
5047                 case S390_ALU_OR:
5048                    buf = s390_emit_LHY(buf, R0, x, b, DISP20(d));
5049                    return s390_emit_OR(buf, dst, R0);
5050     
5051                 case S390_ALU_XOR:
5052                    buf = s390_emit_LHY(buf, R0, x, b, DISP20(d));
5053                    return s390_emit_XR(buf, dst, R0);
5054     
5055                 case S390_ALU_LSH:
5056                 case S390_ALU_RSH:
5057                 case S390_ALU_RSHA: ; /* avoid GCC warning */
5058                 }
5059                 goto fail;
5060              }
5061              goto fail;
5062     
5063           case 4:
5064              switch (src->tag) {
5065              case S390_AMODE_B12:
5066              case S390_AMODE_BX12:
5067                 switch (insn->variant.alu.tag) {
5068                 case S390_ALU_ADD: return s390_emit_A(buf, dst, x, b, d);
5069                 case S390_ALU_SUB: return s390_emit_S(buf, dst, x, b, d);
5070                 case S390_ALU_MUL: return s390_emit_MS(buf, dst, x, b, d);
5071                 case S390_ALU_AND: return s390_emit_N(buf, dst, x, b, d);
5072                 case S390_ALU_OR:  return s390_emit_O(buf, dst, x, b, d);
5073                 case S390_ALU_XOR: return s390_emit_X(buf, dst, x, b, d);
5074                 case S390_ALU_LSH:
5075                 case S390_ALU_RSH:
5076                 case S390_ALU_RSHA: ; /* avoid GCC warning */
5077                 }
5078                 goto fail;
5079     
5080              case S390_AMODE_B20:
5081              case S390_AMODE_BX20:
5082                 switch (insn->variant.alu.tag) {
5083                 case S390_ALU_ADD: return s390_emit_AY(buf, dst, x, b, DISP20(d));
5084                 case S390_ALU_SUB: return s390_emit_SY(buf, dst, x, b, DISP20(d));
5085                 case S390_ALU_MUL: return s390_emit_MSY(buf, dst, x, b, DISP20(d));
5086                 case S390_ALU_AND: return s390_emit_NY(buf, dst, x, b, DISP20(d));
5087                 case S390_ALU_OR:  return s390_emit_OY(buf, dst, x, b, DISP20(d));
5088                 case S390_ALU_XOR: return s390_emit_XY(buf, dst, x, b, DISP20(d));
5089                 case S390_ALU_LSH:
5090                 case S390_ALU_RSH:
5091                 case S390_ALU_RSHA: ; /* avoid GCC warning */
5092                 }
5093                 goto fail;
5094              }
5095              goto fail;
5096     
5097           case 8:
5098              switch (insn->variant.alu.tag) {
5099              case S390_ALU_ADD: return s390_emit_AG(buf, dst, x, b, DISP20(d));
5100              case S390_ALU_SUB: return s390_emit_SG(buf, dst, x, b, DISP20(d));
5101              case S390_ALU_MUL: return s390_emit_MSG(buf, dst, x, b, DISP20(d));
5102              case S390_ALU_AND: return s390_emit_NG(buf, dst, x, b, DISP20(d));
5103              case S390_ALU_OR:  return s390_emit_OG(buf, dst, x, b, DISP20(d));
5104              case S390_ALU_XOR: return s390_emit_XG(buf, dst, x, b, DISP20(d));
5105              case S390_ALU_LSH:
5106              case S390_ALU_RSH:
5107              case S390_ALU_RSHA: ; /* avoid GCC warning */
5108              }
5109              goto fail;
5110           }
5111           goto fail;
5112        }
5113     
5114        /* 2nd operand is an immediate value */
5115        if (op2.tag == S390_OPND_IMMEDIATE) {
5116           ULong value;
5117     
5118           /* No masking of the value is required as it is not sign extended */
5119           value = op2.variant.imm;
5120     
5121           switch (insn->size) {
5122           case 1:
5123           case 2:
5124              /* There is no 1-byte opcode. Do the computation in
5125                 2 bytes. The extra byte will be ignored. */
5126              switch (insn->variant.alu.tag) {
5127              case S390_ALU_ADD:
5128                 return s390_emit_AHI(buf, dst, value);
5129     
5130              case S390_ALU_SUB:
5131                 /* fixs390 later: as an optimization could perhaps use SLFI ? */
5132                 buf = s390_emit_LHI(buf, R0, value);
5133                 return s390_emit_SR(buf, dst, R0);
5134     
5135              case S390_ALU_MUL:
5136                 return s390_emit_MHI(buf, dst, value);
5137     
5138              case S390_ALU_AND: return s390_emit_NILL(buf, dst, value);
5139              case S390_ALU_OR:  return s390_emit_OILL(buf, dst, value);
5140              case S390_ALU_XOR:
5141                 /* There is no XILL instruction.  Load the immediate value into
5142                    R0 and combine with the destination register. */
5143                 buf = s390_emit_LHI(buf, R0, value);
5144                 return s390_emit_XR(buf, dst, R0);
5145     
5146              case S390_ALU_LSH:
5147                 return s390_emit_SLL(buf, dst, 0, value);
5148     
5149              case S390_ALU_RSH:
5150                 return s390_emit_SRL(buf, dst, 0, value);
5151     
5152              case S390_ALU_RSHA:
5153                 return s390_emit_SRA(buf, dst, 0, value);
5154              }
5155              goto fail;
5156     
5157           case 4:
5158              switch (insn->variant.alu.tag) {
5159              case S390_ALU_ADD:
5160                 if (uint_fits_signed_16bit(value)) {
5161                    return s390_emit_AHI(buf, dst, value);
5162                 }
5163                 return s390_emit_AFIw(buf, dst, value);
5164     
5165              case S390_ALU_SUB:  return s390_emit_SLFIw(buf, dst, value);
5166              case S390_ALU_MUL:  return s390_emit_MSFIw(buf, dst, value);
5167              case S390_ALU_AND:  return s390_emit_NILFw(buf, dst, value);
5168              case S390_ALU_OR:   return s390_emit_OILFw(buf, dst, value);
5169              case S390_ALU_XOR:  return s390_emit_XILFw(buf, dst, value);
5170              case S390_ALU_LSH:  return s390_emit_SLL(buf, dst, 0, value);
5171              case S390_ALU_RSH:  return s390_emit_SRL(buf, dst, 0, value);
5172              case S390_ALU_RSHA: return s390_emit_SRA(buf, dst, 0, value);
5173              }
5174              goto fail;
5175     
5176           case 8:
5177              switch (insn->variant.alu.tag) {
5178              case S390_ALU_ADD:
5179                 if (ulong_fits_signed_16bit(value)) {
5180                    return s390_emit_AGHI(buf, dst, value);
5181                 }
5182                 if (ulong_fits_signed_32bit(value) && s390_host_has_eimm) {
5183                    return s390_emit_AGFI(buf, dst, value);
5184                 }
5185                 /* Load constant into R0 then add */
5186                 buf = s390_emit_load_64imm(buf, R0, value);
5187                 return s390_emit_AGR(buf, dst, R0);
5188     
5189              case S390_ALU_SUB:
5190                 /* fixs390 later: as an optimization could perhaps use SLFI ? */
5191                 /* Load value into R0; then subtract from destination reg */
5192                 buf = s390_emit_load_64imm(buf, R0, value);
5193                 return s390_emit_SGR(buf, dst, R0);
5194     
5195              case S390_ALU_MUL:
5196                 if (ulong_fits_signed_32bit(value) && s390_host_has_gie) {
5197                    return s390_emit_MSGFI(buf, dst, value);
5198                 }
5199                 /* Load constant into R0 then add */
5200                 buf = s390_emit_load_64imm(buf, R0, value);
5201                 return s390_emit_MSGR(buf, dst, R0);
5202     
5203                 /* Do it in two steps: upper half [0:31] and lower half [32:63] */
5204              case S390_ALU_AND:
5205                 if (s390_host_has_eimm) {
5206                    buf  = s390_emit_NIHF(buf, dst, value >> 32);
5207                    return s390_emit_NILF(buf, dst, value & 0xFFFFFFFF);
5208                 }
5209                 /* Load value into R0; then combine with destination reg */
5210                 buf = s390_emit_load_64imm(buf, R0, value);
5211                 return s390_emit_NGR(buf, dst, R0);
5212     
5213              case S390_ALU_OR:
5214                 if (s390_host_has_eimm) {
5215                    buf  = s390_emit_OIHF(buf, dst, value >> 32);
5216                    return s390_emit_OILF(buf, dst, value & 0xFFFFFFFF);
5217                 }
5218                 /* Load value into R0; then combine with destination reg */
5219                 buf = s390_emit_load_64imm(buf, R0, value);
5220                 return s390_emit_OGR(buf, dst, R0);
5221     
5222              case S390_ALU_XOR:
5223                 if (s390_host_has_eimm) {
5224                    buf  = s390_emit_XIHF(buf, dst, value >> 32);
5225                    return s390_emit_XILF(buf, dst, value & 0xFFFFFFFF);
5226                 }
5227                 /* Load value into R0; then combine with destination reg */
5228                 buf = s390_emit_load_64imm(buf, R0, value);
5229                 return s390_emit_XGR(buf, dst, R0);
5230     
5231              case S390_ALU_LSH:  return s390_emit_SLLG(buf, dst, dst, 0, DISP20(value));
5232              case S390_ALU_RSH:  return s390_emit_SRLG(buf, dst, dst, 0, DISP20(value));
5233              case S390_ALU_RSHA: return s390_emit_SRAG(buf, dst, dst, 0, DISP20(value));
5234              }
5235              goto fail;
5236           }
5237           goto fail;
5238        }
5239     
5240      fail:
5241        vpanic("s390_insn_alu_emit");
5242     }
5243     
5244     
5245     static UChar *
5246     s390_widen_emit(UChar *buf, const s390_insn *insn, UInt from_size,
5247                     Bool sign_extend)
5248     {
5249        s390_opnd_RMI opnd = insn->variant.unop.src;
5250     
5251        switch (opnd.tag) {
5252        case S390_OPND_REG: {
5253           UChar r1 = hregNumber(insn->variant.unop.dst);
5254           UChar r2 = hregNumber(opnd.variant.reg);
5255     
5256           switch (from_size) {
5257           case 1:
5258              /* Widening to a half-word is implemented like widening to a word
5259                 because the upper half-word will not be looked at. */
5260              if (insn->size == 4 || insn->size == 2) {  /* 8 --> 32    8 --> 16 */
5261                 if (sign_extend)
5262                    return s390_emit_LBRw(buf, r1, r2);
5263                 else
5264                    return s390_emit_LLCRw(buf, r1, r2);
5265              }
5266              if (insn->size == 8) {  /* 8 --> 64 */
5267                 if (sign_extend)
5268                    return s390_emit_LGBRw(buf, r1, r2);
5269                 else
5270                    return s390_emit_LLGCRw(buf, r1, r2);
5271              }
5272              goto fail;
5273     
5274           case 2:
5275              if (insn->size == 4) {  /* 16 --> 32 */
5276                 if (sign_extend)
5277                    return s390_emit_LHRw(buf, r1, r2);
5278                 else
5279                    return s390_emit_LLHRw(buf, r1, r2);
5280              }
5281              if (insn->size == 8) {  /* 16 --> 64 */
5282                 if (sign_extend)
5283                    return s390_emit_LGHRw(buf, r1, r2);
5284                 else
5285                    return s390_emit_LLGHRw(buf, r1, r2);
5286              }
5287              goto fail;
5288     
5289           case 4:
5290              if (insn->size == 8) {  /* 32 --> 64 */
5291                 if (sign_extend)
5292                    return s390_emit_LGFR(buf, r1, r2);
5293                 else
5294                    return s390_emit_LLGFR(buf, r1, r2);
5295              }
5296              goto fail;
5297     
5298           default: /* unexpected "from" size */
5299              goto fail;
5300           }
5301        }
5302     
5303        case S390_OPND_AMODE: {
5304           UChar r1 = hregNumber(insn->variant.unop.dst);
5305           const s390_amode *src = opnd.variant.am;
5306           UChar b = hregNumber(src->b);
5307           UChar x = hregNumber(src->x);
5308           Int   d = src->d;
5309     
5310           switch (from_size) {
5311           case 1:
5312              if (insn->size == 4 || insn->size == 2) {
5313                 if (sign_extend)
5314                    return s390_emit_LB(buf, r1, x, b, DISP20(d));
5315                 else
5316                    return s390_emit_LLCw(buf, r1, x, b, DISP20(d));
5317              }
5318              if (insn->size == 8) {
5319                 if (sign_extend)
5320                    return s390_emit_LGB(buf, r1, x, b, DISP20(d));
5321                 else
5322                    /* No wrapper required. Opcode exists as RXE and RXY */
5323                    return s390_emit_LLGC(buf, r1, x, b, DISP20(d));
5324              }
5325              goto fail;
5326     
5327           case 2:
5328              if (insn->size == 4) {  /* 16 --> 32 */
5329                 if (sign_extend == 0)
5330                    return s390_emit_LLHw(buf, r1, x, b, DISP20(d));
5331     
5332                 switch (src->tag) {
5333                 case S390_AMODE_B12:
5334                 case S390_AMODE_BX12:
5335                    return s390_emit_LH(buf, r1, x, b, d);
5336     
5337                 case S390_AMODE_B20:
5338                 case S390_AMODE_BX20:
5339                    return s390_emit_LHY(buf, r1, x, b, DISP20(d));
5340                 }
5341                 goto fail;
5342              }
5343              if (insn->size == 8) {  /* 16 --> 64 */
5344                 /* No wrappers required. Opcodes exist as RXE and RXY */
5345                 if (sign_extend)
5346                    return s390_emit_LGH(buf, r1, x, b, DISP20(d));
5347                 else
5348                    return s390_emit_LLGH(buf, r1, x, b, DISP20(d));
5349              }
5350              goto fail;
5351     
5352           case 4:
5353              if (insn->size == 8) {  /* 32 --> 64 */
5354                 /* No wrappers required. Opcodes exist as RXE and RXY */
5355                 if (sign_extend)
5356                    return s390_emit_LGF(buf, r1, x, b, DISP20(d));
5357                 else
5358                    return s390_emit_LLGF(buf, r1, x, b, DISP20(d));
5359              }
5360              goto fail;
5361     
5362           default: /* unexpected "from" size */
5363              goto fail;
5364           }
5365        }
5366     
5367        case S390_OPND_IMMEDIATE: {
5368           UChar r1 = hregNumber(insn->variant.unop.dst);
5369           ULong value = opnd.variant.imm;
5370     
5371           switch (from_size) {
5372           case 1:
5373              if (insn->size == 4 || insn->size == 2) {  /* 8 --> 32   8 --> 16 */
5374                 if (sign_extend) {
5375                    /* host can do the sign extension to 16-bit; LHI does the rest */
5376                    return s390_emit_LHI(buf, r1, (Short)(Char)(UChar)value);
5377                 } else {
5378                    return s390_emit_LHI(buf, r1, value);
5379                 }
5380              }
5381              if (insn->size == 8) {  /* 8 --> 64 */
5382                 if (sign_extend) {
5383                    /* host can do the sign extension to 16-bit; LGHI does the rest */
5384                    return s390_emit_LGHI(buf, r1, (Short)(Char)(UChar)value);
5385                 } else {
5386                    return s390_emit_LGHI(buf, r1, value);
5387                 }
5388              }
5389              goto fail;
5390     
5391           case 2:
5392              if (insn->size == 4) {  /* 16 --> 32 */
5393                 return s390_emit_LHI(buf, r1, value);
5394              }
5395              if (insn->size == 8) {  /* 16 --> 64 */
5396                 if (sign_extend)
5397                    return s390_emit_LGHI(buf, r1, value);
5398                 else
5399                    return s390_emit_LLILL(buf, r1, value);
5400              }
5401              goto fail;
5402     
5403           case 4:
5404              if (insn->size == 8) {  /* 32 --> 64 */
5405                 if (sign_extend)
5406                    return s390_emit_LGFIw(buf, r1, value);
5407                 else
5408                    return s390_emit_LLILFw(buf, r1, value);
5409              }
5410              goto fail;
5411     
5412           default: /* unexpected "from" size */
5413              goto fail;
5414           }
5415        }
5416        }
5417     
5418      fail:
5419        vpanic("s390_widen_emit");
5420     }
5421     
5422     
5423     static UChar *
5424     s390_negate_emit(UChar *buf, const s390_insn *insn)
5425     {
5426        s390_opnd_RMI opnd;
5427     
5428        opnd = insn->variant.unop.src;
5429     
5430        switch (opnd.tag) {
5431        case S390_OPND_REG: {
5432           UChar r1 = hregNumber(insn->variant.unop.dst);
5433           UChar r2 = hregNumber(opnd.variant.reg);
5434     
5435           switch (insn->size) {
5436           case 1:
5437           case 2:
5438           case 4:
5439              return s390_emit_LCR(buf, r1, r2);
5440     
5441           case 8:
5442              return s390_emit_LCGR(buf, r1, r2);
5443     
5444           default:
5445              goto fail;
5446           }
5447        }
5448     
5449        case S390_OPND_AMODE: {
5450           UChar r1 = hregNumber(insn->variant.unop.dst);
5451     
5452           /* Load bytes into scratch register R0, then negate */
5453           buf = s390_emit_load_mem(buf, insn->size, R0, opnd.variant.am);
5454     
5455           switch (insn->size) {
5456           case 1:
5457           case 2:
5458           case 4:
5459              return s390_emit_LCR(buf, r1, R0);
5460     
5461           case 8:
5462              return s390_emit_LCGR(buf, r1, R0);
5463     
5464           default:
5465              goto fail;
5466           }
5467        }
5468     
5469        case S390_OPND_IMMEDIATE: {
5470           UChar r1 = hregNumber(insn->variant.unop.dst);
5471           ULong value = opnd.variant.imm;
5472     
5473           value = ~value + 1;   /* two's complement */
5474     
5475           switch (insn->size) {
5476           case 1:
5477           case 2:
5478              /* Load the immediate values as a 4 byte value. That does not hurt as
5479                 those extra bytes will not be looked at. Fall through .... */
5480           case 4:
5481              return s390_emit_load_32imm(buf, r1, value);
5482     
5483           case 8:
5484              return s390_emit_load_64imm(buf, r1, value);
5485     
5486           default:
5487              goto fail;
5488           }
5489        }
5490        }
5491     
5492      fail:
5493        vpanic("s390_negate_emit");
5494     }
5495     
5496     
5497     static UChar *
5498     s390_insn_unop_emit(UChar *buf, const s390_insn *insn)
5499     {
5500        switch (insn->variant.unop.tag) {
5501        case S390_ZERO_EXTEND_8:  return s390_widen_emit(buf, insn, 1, 0);
5502        case S390_ZERO_EXTEND_16: return s390_widen_emit(buf, insn, 2, 0);
5503        case S390_ZERO_EXTEND_32: return s390_widen_emit(buf, insn, 4, 0);
5504     
5505        case S390_SIGN_EXTEND_8:  return s390_widen_emit(buf, insn, 1, 1);
5506        case S390_SIGN_EXTEND_16: return s390_widen_emit(buf, insn, 2, 1);
5507        case S390_SIGN_EXTEND_32: return s390_widen_emit(buf, insn, 4, 1);
5508     
5509        case S390_NEGATE:         return s390_negate_emit(buf, insn);
5510        }
5511     
5512        vpanic("s390_insn_unop_emit");
5513     }

5516     /* Only 4-byte and 8-byte operands are handled. 1-byte and 2-byte
5517        comparisons will have been converted to 4-byte comparisons in
5518        s390_isel_cc and should not occur here. */
5519     static UChar *
5520     s390_insn_test_emit(UChar *buf, const s390_insn *insn)
5521     {
5522        s390_opnd_RMI opnd;
5523     
5524        opnd = insn->variant.test.src;
5525     
5526        switch (opnd.tag) {
5527        case S390_OPND_REG: {
5528           UInt reg = hregNumber(opnd.variant.reg);
5529     
5530           switch (insn->size) {
5531           case 4:
5532              return s390_emit_LTR(buf, reg, reg);
5533     
5534           case 8:
5535              return s390_emit_LTGR(buf, reg, reg);
5536     
5537           default:
5538              goto fail;
5539           }
5540        }
5541     
5542        case S390_OPND_AMODE: {
5543           const s390_amode *am = opnd.variant.am;
5544           UChar b = hregNumber(am->b);
5545           UChar x = hregNumber(am->x);
5546           Int   d = am->d;
5547     
5548           switch (insn->size) {
5549           case 4:
5550              return s390_emit_LTw(buf, R0, x, b, DISP20(d));
5551     
5552           case 8:
5553              return s390_emit_LTGw(buf, R0, x, b, DISP20(d));
5554     
5555           default:
5556              goto fail;
5557           }
5558        }
5559     
5560        case S390_OPND_IMMEDIATE: {
5561           ULong value = opnd.variant.imm;
5562     
5563           switch (insn->size) {
5564           case 4:
5565              buf = s390_emit_load_32imm(buf, R0, value);
5566              return s390_emit_LTR(buf, R0, R0);
5567     
5568           case 8:
5569              buf = s390_emit_load_64imm(buf, R0, value);
5570              return s390_emit_LTGR(buf, R0, R0);
5571     
5572           default:
5573              goto fail;
5574           }
5575        }
5576     
5577        default:
5578           goto fail;
5579        }
5580     
5581      fail:
5582        vpanic("s390_insn_test_emit");
5583     }

5586     static UChar *
5587     s390_insn_cc2bool_emit(UChar *buf, const s390_insn *insn)
5588     {
5589        UChar r1 = hregNumber(insn->variant.cc2bool.dst);
5590        s390_cc_t cond = insn->variant.cc2bool.cond;
5591     
5592        /* Make the destination register be 1 or 0, depending on whether
5593           the relevant condition holds. A 64-bit value is computed. */
5594        if (cond == S390_CC_ALWAYS)
5595           return s390_emit_LGHI(buf, r1, 1);  /* r1 = 1 */
5596     
5597        buf = s390_emit_load_cc(buf, r1);                 /* r1 = cc */
5598        buf = s390_emit_LGHI(buf, R0, cond);              /* r0 = mask */
5599        buf = s390_emit_SLLG(buf, r1, R0, r1, DISP20(0)); /* r1 = mask << cc */
5600        buf = s390_emit_SRLG(buf, r1, r1, 0,  DISP20(3)); /* r1 = r1 >> 3 */
5601        buf = s390_emit_NILL(buf, r1, 1);                 /* r1 = r1 & 0x1 */
5602     
5603        return buf;
5604     }

5606     
5607     /* Only 4-byte and 8-byte operands are handled. */
5608     static UChar *
5609     s390_insn_cas_emit(UChar *buf, const s390_insn *insn)
5610     {
5611        UChar r1, r3, b, old;
5612        Int d;
5613        s390_amode *am;
5614     
5615        r1 = hregNumber(insn->variant.cas.op1); /* expected value */
5616        r3 = hregNumber(insn->variant.cas.op3);
5617        old= hregNumber(insn->variant.cas.old_mem);
5618        am = insn->variant.cas.op2;
5619        b  = hregNumber(am->b);
5620        d  = am->d;
5621     
5622        switch (insn->size) {
5623        case 4:
5624           /* r1 must no be overwritten. So copy it to R0 and let CS clobber it */
5625           buf = s390_emit_LR(buf, R0, r1);
5626           if (am->tag == S390_AMODE_B12)
5627              buf = s390_emit_CS(buf, R0, r3, b, d);
5628           else
5629              buf = s390_emit_CSY(buf, R0, r3, b, DISP20(d));
5630           /* Now copy R0 which has the old memory value to OLD */
5631           return s390_emit_LR(buf, old, R0);
5632     
5633        case 8:
5634           /* r1 must no be overwritten. So copy it to R0 and let CS clobber it */
5635           buf = s390_emit_LGR(buf, R0, r1);
5636           buf = s390_emit_CSG(buf, R0, r3, b, DISP20(d));
5637           /* Now copy R0 which has the old memory value to OLD */
5638           return s390_emit_LGR(buf, old, R0);
5639     
5640        default:
5641           goto fail;
5642        }
5643     
5644      fail:
5645        vpanic("s390_insn_cas_emit");
5646     }
5647     
5648     
5649     /* Only 4-byte and 8-byte comparisons are handled. 1-byte and 2-byte
5650        comparisons will have been converted to 4-byte comparisons in
5651        s390_isel_cc and should not occur here. */
5652     static UChar *
5653     s390_insn_compare_emit(UChar *buf, const s390_insn *insn)
5654     {
5655        s390_opnd_RMI op2;
5656        HReg op1;
5657        Bool signed_comparison;
5658     
5659        op1 = insn->variant.compare.src1;
5660        op2 = insn->variant.compare.src2;
5661        signed_comparison = insn->variant.compare.signed_comparison;
5662     
5663        switch (op2.tag) {
5664        case S390_OPND_REG: {
5665           UInt r1 = hregNumber(op1);
5666           UInt r2 = hregNumber(op2.variant.reg);
5667     
5668           switch (insn->size) {
5669           case 4:
5670              if (signed_comparison)
5671                 return s390_emit_CR(buf, r1, r2);
5672              else
5673                 return s390_emit_CLR(buf, r1, r2);
5674     
5675           case 8:
5676              if (signed_comparison)
5677                 return s390_emit_CGR(buf, r1, r2);
5678              else
5679                 return s390_emit_CLGR(buf, r1, r2);
5680     
5681           default:
5682              goto fail;
5683           }
5684        }
5685     
5686        case S390_OPND_AMODE: {
5687           UChar r1 = hregNumber(op1);
5688           const s390_amode *am = op2.variant.am;
5689           UChar b = hregNumber(am->b);
5690           UChar x = hregNumber(am->x);
5691           Int   d = am->d;
5692     
5693           switch (insn->size) {
5694           case 4:
5695              switch (am->tag) {
5696              case S390_AMODE_B12:
5697              case S390_AMODE_BX12:
5698                 if (signed_comparison)
5699                    return s390_emit_C(buf, r1, x, b, d);
5700                 else
5701                    return s390_emit_CL(buf, r1, x, b, d);
5702     
5703              case S390_AMODE_B20:
5704              case S390_AMODE_BX20:
5705                 if (signed_comparison)
5706                    return s390_emit_CY(buf, r1, x, b, DISP20(d));
5707                 else
5708                    return s390_emit_CLY(buf, r1, x, b, DISP20(d));
5709              }
5710              goto fail;
5711     
5712           case 8:
5713              if (signed_comparison)
5714                 return s390_emit_CG(buf, r1, x, b, DISP20(d));
5715              else
5716                 return s390_emit_CLG(buf, r1, x, b, DISP20(d));
5717     
5718           default:
5719              goto fail;
5720           }
5721        }
5722     
5723        case S390_OPND_IMMEDIATE: {
5724           UChar r1 = hregNumber(op1);
5725           ULong value = op2.variant.imm;
5726     
5727           switch (insn->size) {
5728           case 4:
5729              if (signed_comparison)
5730                 return s390_emit_CFIw(buf, r1, value);
5731              else
5732                 return s390_emit_CLFIw(buf, r1, value);
5733     
5734           case 8:
5735              buf = s390_emit_load_64imm(buf, R0, value);
5736              if (signed_comparison)
5737                 return s390_emit_CGR(buf, r1, R0);
5738              else
5739                 return s390_emit_CLGR(buf, r1, R0);
5740     
5741           default:
5742              goto fail;
5743           }
5744        }
5745     
5746        default:
5747           goto fail;
5748        }
5749     
5750      fail:
5751        vpanic("s390_insn_compare_emit");
5752     }

5754     
5755     static UChar *
5756     s390_insn_mul_emit(UChar *buf, const s390_insn *insn)
5757     {
5758        s390_opnd_RMI op2;
5759        UChar r1;
5760        Bool signed_multiply;
5761     
5762        /* The register number identifying the register pair */
5763        r1  = hregNumber(insn->variant.mul.dst_hi);
5764     
5765        op2 = insn->variant.mul.op2;
5766        signed_multiply = insn->variant.mul.signed_multiply;
5767     
5768        switch (op2.tag) {
5769        case S390_OPND_REG: {
5770           UInt r2 = hregNumber(op2.variant.reg);
5771     
5772           switch (insn->size) {
5773           case 1:
5774           case 2:
5775           case 4:
5776              if (signed_multiply)
5777                 return s390_emit_MR(buf, r1, r2);
5778              else
5779                 return s390_emit_MLR(buf, r1, r2);
5780     
5781           case 8:
5782              if (signed_multiply)
5783                 vpanic("s390_insn_mul_emit");
5784              else
5785                 return s390_emit_MLGR(buf, r1, r2);
5786     
5787           default:
5788              goto fail;
5789           }
5790        }
5791     
5792        case S390_OPND_AMODE: {
5793           const s390_amode *am = op2.variant.am;
5794           UChar b = hregNumber(am->b);
5795           UChar x = hregNumber(am->x);
5796           Int   d = am->d;
5797     
5798           switch (insn->size) {
5799           case 1:
5800           case 2:
5801              /* Load bytes into scratch register R0, then multiply */
5802              buf = s390_emit_load_mem(buf, insn->size, R0, am);
5803              if (signed_multiply)
5804                 return s390_emit_MR(buf, r1, R0);
5805              else
5806                 return s390_emit_MLR(buf, r1, R0);
5807     
5808           case 4:
5809              switch (am->tag) {
5810              case S390_AMODE_B12:
5811              case S390_AMODE_BX12:
5812                 if (signed_multiply)
5813                    return s390_emit_M(buf, r1, x, b, d);
5814                 else
5815                    return s390_emit_ML(buf, r1, x, b, DISP20(d));
5816     
5817              case S390_AMODE_B20:
5818              case S390_AMODE_BX20:
5819                 if (signed_multiply)
5820                    return s390_emit_MFYw(buf, r1, x, b, DISP20(d));
5821                 else
5822                    vpanic("s390_insn_mul_emit");
5823              }
5824              goto fail;
5825     
5826           case 8:
5827              if (signed_multiply)
5828                 vpanic("s390_insn_mul_emit");
5829              else
5830                 return s390_emit_MLG(buf, r1, x, b, DISP20(d));
5831     
5832           default:
5833              goto fail;
5834           }
5835        }
5836     
5837        case S390_OPND_IMMEDIATE: {
5838           ULong value = op2.variant.imm;
5839     
5840           switch (insn->size) {
5841           case 1:
5842           case 2:
5843           case 4:
5844              buf = s390_emit_load_32imm(buf, R0, value);
5845              if (signed_multiply)
5846                 return s390_emit_MR(buf, r1, R0);
5847              else
5848                 return s390_emit_MLR(buf, r1, R0);
5849     
5850           case 8:
5851              buf = s390_emit_load_64imm(buf, R0, value);
5852              if (signed_multiply)
5853                 vpanic("s390_insn_mul_emit");
5854              else
5855                 return s390_emit_MLGR(buf, r1, R0);
5856     
5857           default:
5858              goto fail;
5859           }
5860        }
5861     
5862        default:
5863           goto fail;
5864        }
5865     
5866      fail:
5867        vpanic("s390_insn_mul_emit");
5868     }

5871     static UChar *
5872     s390_insn_div_emit(UChar *buf, const s390_insn *insn)
5873     {
5874        s390_opnd_RMI op2;
5875        UChar r1;
5876        Bool signed_divide;
5877     
5878        r1  = hregNumber(insn->variant.div.op1_hi);
5879        op2 = insn->variant.div.op2;
5880        signed_divide = insn->variant.div.signed_divide;
5881     
5882        switch (op2.tag) {
5883        case S390_OPND_REG: {
5884           UInt r2 = hregNumber(op2.variant.reg);
5885     
5886           switch (insn->size) {
5887           case 4:
5888              if (signed_divide)
5889                 return s390_emit_DR(buf, r1, r2);
5890              else
5891                 return s390_emit_DLR(buf, r1, r2);
5892     
5893           case 8:
5894              if (signed_divide)
5895                 vpanic("s390_insn_div_emit");
5896              else
5897                 return s390_emit_DLGR(buf, r1, r2);
5898     
5899           default:
5900              goto fail;
5901           }
5902        }
5903     
5904        case S390_OPND_AMODE: {
5905           const s390_amode *am = op2.variant.am;
5906           UChar b = hregNumber(am->b);
5907           UChar x = hregNumber(am->x);
5908           Int   d = am->d;
5909     
5910           switch (insn->size) {
5911           case 4:
5912              switch (am->tag) {
5913              case S390_AMODE_B12:
5914              case S390_AMODE_BX12:
5915                 if (signed_divide)
5916                    return s390_emit_D(buf, r1, x, b, d);
5917                 else
5918                    return s390_emit_DL(buf, r1, x, b, DISP20(d));
5919     
5920              case S390_AMODE_B20:
5921              case S390_AMODE_BX20:
5922                 buf = s390_emit_LY(buf, R0, x, b, DISP20(d));
5923                 if (signed_divide)
5924                    return s390_emit_DR(buf, r1, R0);
5925                 else
5926                    return s390_emit_DLR(buf, r1, R0);
5927              }
5928              goto fail;
5929     
5930           case 8:
5931              if (signed_divide)
5932                 vpanic("s390_insn_div_emit");
5933              else
5934                 return s390_emit_DLG(buf, r1, x, b, DISP20(d));
5935     
5936           default:
5937              goto fail;
5938           }
5939        }
5940     
5941        case S390_OPND_IMMEDIATE: {
5942           ULong value = op2.variant.imm;
5943     
5944           switch (insn->size) {
5945           case 4:
5946              buf = s390_emit_load_32imm(buf, R0, value);
5947              if (signed_divide)
5948                 return s390_emit_DR(buf, r1, R0);
5949              else
5950                 return s390_emit_DLR(buf, r1, R0);
5951     
5952           case 8:
5953              buf = s390_emit_load_64imm(buf, R0, value);
5954              if (signed_divide)
5955                 vpanic("s390_insn_div_emit");
5956              else
5957                 return s390_emit_DLGR(buf, r1, R0);
5958     
5959           default:
5960              goto fail;
5961           }
5962        }
5963     
5964        default:
5965           goto fail;
5966        }
5967     
5968      fail:
5969        vpanic("s390_insn_div_emit");
5970     }

5973     static UChar *
5974     s390_insn_divs_emit(UChar *buf, const s390_insn *insn)
5975     {
5976        s390_opnd_RMI op2;
5977        UChar r1;
5978

5980        op2 = insn->variant.divs.op2;
5981

5984           UInt r2 = hregNumber(op2.variant.reg);
5985     
5986           return s390_emit_DSGR(buf, r1, r2);
5987        }
5988     
5989        case S390_OPND_AMODE: {
5990           const s390_amode *am = op2.variant.am;

5999           ULong value = op2.variant.imm;
6000

6002           return s390_emit_DSGR(buf, r1, R0);
6003        }
6004     
6005        default:
6006           goto fail;
6007        }
6008     
6009      fail:
6010        vpanic("s390_insn_divs_emit");
