6013     
6014     static UChar *
6015     s390_insn_clz_emit(UChar *buf, const s390_insn *insn)
6016     {
6017        s390_opnd_RMI src;
6018        UChar r1, r1p1, r2, *p;
6019     
6020        r1   = hregNumber(insn->variant.clz.num_bits);
6021        r1p1 = hregNumber(insn->variant.clz.clobber);
6022     
6023        vassert((r1 & 0x1) == 0);
6024        vassert(r1p1 == r1 + 1);
6025     
6026        p = buf;
6027        src = insn->variant.clz.src;
6028     
6029        /* Get operand and move it to r2 */
6030        switch (src.tag) {
6031        case S390_OPND_REG:
6032           r2 = hregNumber(src.variant.reg);
6033           break;
6034     
6035        case S390_OPND_AMODE: {
6036           const s390_amode *am = src.variant.am;
6037           UChar b = hregNumber(am->b);
6038           UChar x = hregNumber(am->x);
6039           Int   d = am->d;
6040     
6041           p  = s390_emit_LG(p, R0, x, b, DISP20(d));
6042           r2 = R0;
6043           break;
6044        }
6045     
6046        case S390_OPND_IMMEDIATE: {
6047           ULong value = src.variant.imm;
6048     
6049           p  = s390_emit_load_64imm(p, R0, value);
6050           r2 = R0;
6051           break;
6052        }
6053     
6054        default:
6055           goto fail;
6056        }
6057     
6058        /* Use FLOGR if you can */
6059        if (s390_host_has_eimm) {
6060           return s390_emit_FLOGR(p, r1, r2);
6061        }
6062     
6063        /*
6064           r0 = r2;
6065           r1 = 64;
6066           while (r0 != 0) {
6067             r1 -= 1;
6068             r0 >>= 1;
6069           }
6070        */
6071        p = s390_emit_LTGR(p, R0, r2);
6072        p = s390_emit_LLILL(p, r1,  64);
6073     
6074        p = s390_emit_BRC(p, S390_CC_E, (4 + 4 + 6 + 4 + 4)/ 2);  /* 4 bytes */
6075        p = s390_emit_AGHI(p, r1, (UShort)-1);         /* r1  -= 1;  4 bytes */
6076        p = s390_emit_SRLG(p, R0, R0, R0, DISP20(1));  /* r0 >>= 1;  6 bytes */
6077        p = s390_emit_LTGR(p, R0, R0);                 /* set cc     4 bytes */
6078        p = s390_emit_BRC(p, S390_CC_NE,               /*            4 bytes */
6079                          (UShort)(-(4 + 6 + 4) / 2));
6080        return p;
6081     
6082      fail:
6083        vpanic("s390_insn_clz_emit");
6084     }
6085     
6086     
6087     static UChar *
6088     s390_insn_branch_emit(UChar *buf, const s390_insn *insn)
6089     {
6090        s390_opnd_RMI dst;
6091        s390_cc_t cond;
6092        UInt       trc;
6093        UChar *p, *ptmp = 0;  /* avoid compiler warnings */
6094     
6095        cond = insn->variant.branch.cond;
6096        dst  = insn->variant.branch.dst;
6097     
6098        p = buf;
6099        trc = 0;
6100     
6101        if (cond != S390_CC_ALWAYS) {
6102           /* So we have something like this
6103              if (cond) goto X;
6104              Y: ...
6105              We convert this into
6106              if (! cond) goto Y;        // BRC insn; 4 bytes
6107              return_reg = X;
6108              return to dispatcher
6109              Y:
6110           */
6111           ptmp = p; /* 4 bytes (a BRC insn) to be filled in here */
6112           p += 4;
6113        }
6114     
6115        /* If a non-boring, set guest-state-pointer appropriately. */
6116     
6117        switch (insn->variant.branch.kind) {
6118        case Ijk_ClientReq:   trc = VEX_TRC_JMP_CLIENTREQ;   break;
6119        case Ijk_Sys_syscall: trc = VEX_TRC_JMP_SYS_SYSCALL; break;
6120        case Ijk_Yield:       trc = VEX_TRC_JMP_YIELD;       break;
6121        case Ijk_EmWarn:      trc = VEX_TRC_JMP_EMWARN;      break;
6122        case Ijk_EmFail:      trc = VEX_TRC_JMP_EMFAIL;      break;
6123        case Ijk_MapFail:     trc = VEX_TRC_JMP_MAPFAIL;     break;
6124        case Ijk_NoDecode:    trc = VEX_TRC_JMP_NODECODE;    break;
6125        case Ijk_TInval:      trc = VEX_TRC_JMP_TINVAL;      break;
6126        case Ijk_NoRedir:     trc = VEX_TRC_JMP_NOREDIR;     break;
6127        case Ijk_SigTRAP:     trc = VEX_TRC_JMP_SIGTRAP;     break;
6128        case Ijk_Ret:         trc = 0; break;
6129        case Ijk_Call:        trc = 0; break;
6130        case Ijk_Boring:      trc = 0; break;
6131           break;
6132     
6133        default:
6134           vpanic("s390_insn_branch_emit: unknown jump kind");
6135        }
6136     
6137        /* Get the destination address into the return register */
6138        switch (dst.tag) {
6139        case S390_OPND_REG:
6140           p = s390_emit_LGR(p, S390_REGNO_RETURN_VALUE, hregNumber(dst.variant.reg));
6141           break;
6142     
6143        case S390_OPND_AMODE: {
6144           const s390_amode *am = dst.variant.am;
6145           UChar b = hregNumber(am->b);
6146           UChar x = hregNumber(am->x);
6147           Int   d = am->d;
6148     
6149           p = s390_emit_LG(p, S390_REGNO_RETURN_VALUE, x, b, DISP20(d));
6150           break;
6151        }
6152     
6153        case S390_OPND_IMMEDIATE:
6154           p = s390_emit_load_64imm(p, S390_REGNO_RETURN_VALUE, dst.variant.imm);
6155           break;
6156     
6157        default:
6158           goto fail;
6159        }
6160     
6161        if (trc != 0) {
6162           /* Something special. Set guest-state pointer appropriately */
6163           p = s390_emit_LGHI(p, S390_REGNO_GUEST_STATE_POINTER, trc);
6164        } else {
6165           /* Nothing special needs to be done for calls and returns. */
6166        }
6167     
6168        p = s390_emit_BCR(p, S390_CC_ALWAYS, S390_REGNO_LINK_REGISTER);
6169     
6170        if (cond != S390_CC_ALWAYS) {
6171           Int delta = p - ptmp;
6172     
6173           delta >>= 1;  /* immediate constant is #half-words */
6174           vassert(delta > 0 && delta < (1 << 16));
6175           s390_emit_BRC(ptmp, s390_cc_invert(cond), delta);
6176        }
6177     
6178        return p;
6179     
6180      fail:
6181        vpanic("s390_insn_branch_emit");
6182     }
6183     
6184     
6185     static UChar *
6186     s390_insn_helper_call_emit(UChar *buf, const s390_insn *insn)
6187     {
6188        s390_cc_t cond;
6189        ULong target;
6190        UChar *ptmp = buf;
6191     
6192        cond = insn->variant.helper_call.cond;
6193        target = insn->variant.helper_call.target;
6194     
6195        if (cond != S390_CC_ALWAYS) {
6196           /* So we have something like this
6197              if (cond) call X;
6198              Y: ...
6199              We convert this into
6200              if (! cond) goto Y;        // BRC opcode; 4 bytes
6201              call X;
6202              Y:
6203           */
6204           /* 4 bytes (a BRC insn) to be filled in here */
6205           buf += 4;
6206        }
6207     
6208        /* Load the target address into a register, that
6209           (a) is not used for passing parameters to the helper and
6210           (b) can be clobbered by the callee
6211           r1 looks like a good choice.
6212           Also, need to arrange for the return address be put into the
6213           link-register */
6214        buf = s390_emit_load_64imm(buf, 1, target);
6215     
6216        /* Stash away the client's FPC register because the helper might change it. */
6217        buf = s390_emit_STFPC(buf, S390_REGNO_STACK_POINTER, S390_OFFSET_SAVED_FPC_C);
6218     
6219        /* Before we can call the helper, we need to save the link register,
6220           because the BASR will overwrite it. We cannot use a register for that.
6221           (a) Volatile registers will be modified by the helper.
6222           (b) For saved registers the client code assumes that they have not
6223               changed after the function returns. So we cannot use it to store
6224               the link register.
6225           In the dispatcher, before calling the client code, we have arranged for
6226           a location on the stack for this purpose. See dispatch-s390x-linux.S. */
6227        buf = s390_emit_STG(buf, S390_REGNO_LINK_REGISTER, 0,        // save LR
6228                            S390_REGNO_STACK_POINTER, S390_OFFSET_SAVED_LR, 0);
6229        buf = s390_emit_BASR(buf, S390_REGNO_LINK_REGISTER, 1);      // call helper
6230        buf = s390_emit_LG(buf, S390_REGNO_LINK_REGISTER, 0,         // restore LR
6231                           S390_REGNO_STACK_POINTER, S390_OFFSET_SAVED_LR, 0);
6232        buf = s390_emit_LFPC(buf, S390_REGNO_STACK_POINTER,          // restore FPC
6233                             S390_OFFSET_SAVED_FPC_C);
6234     
6235        if (cond != S390_CC_ALWAYS) {
6236           Int delta = buf - ptmp;
6237     
6238           delta >>= 1;  /* immediate constant is #half-words */
6239           vassert(delta > 0 && delta < (1 << 16));
6240           s390_emit_BRC(ptmp, s390_cc_invert(cond), delta);
6241        }
6242     
6243        return buf;
6244     }
6245     
6246     
6247     static UChar *
6248     s390_insn_cond_move_emit(UChar *buf, const s390_insn *insn)
6249     {
6250        HReg dst;
6251        s390_opnd_RMI src;
6252        s390_cc_t cond;
6253        UChar *p, *ptmp = 0;   /* avoid compiler warnings */
6254     
6255        cond = insn->variant.cond_move.cond;
6256        dst  = insn->variant.cond_move.dst;
6257        src  = insn->variant.cond_move.src;
6258     
6259        p = buf;
6260     
6261        /* Branch (if cond fails) over move instrs */
6262        if (cond != S390_CC_ALWAYS) {
6263           /* Don't know how many bytes to jump over yet.
6264              Make space for a BRC instruction (4 bytes) and fill in later. */
6265           ptmp = p;   /*  to be filled in here */
6266           p += 4;
6267        }
6268     
6269        // cond true: move src => dst
6270     
6271        switch (src.tag) {
6272        case S390_OPND_REG:
6273           p = s390_emit_LGR(p, hregNumber(dst), hregNumber(src.variant.reg));
6274           break;
6275     
6276        case S390_OPND_AMODE:
6277           p = s390_emit_load_mem(p, insn->size, hregNumber(dst), src.variant.am);
6278           break;
6279     
6280        case S390_OPND_IMMEDIATE: {
6281           ULong value = src.variant.imm;
6282           UInt  r = hregNumber(dst);
6283     
6284           switch (insn->size) {
6285           case 1:
6286           case 2:
6287              /* Load the immediate values as a 4 byte value. That does not hurt as
6288                 those extra bytes will not be looked at. Fall through .... */
6289           case 4:
6290              p = s390_emit_load_32imm(p, r, value);
6291              break;
6292     
6293           case 8:
6294              p = s390_emit_load_64imm(p, r, value);
6295              break;
6296           }
6297           break;
6298        }
6299     
6300        default:
6301           goto fail;
6302        }
6303     
6304        if (cond != S390_CC_ALWAYS) {
6305           Int delta = p - ptmp;
6306     
6307           delta >>= 1;  /* immediate constant is #half-words */
6308           vassert(delta > 0 && delta < (1 << 16));
6309           s390_emit_BRC(ptmp, s390_cc_invert(cond), delta);
6310        }
6311     
6312        return p;
6313     
6314      fail:
6315        vpanic("s390_insn_cond_move_emit");
6316     }
6317     
6318     
6319     /* Little helper function to the rounding mode in the real FPC
6320        register */
6321     static UChar *
6322     s390_set_fpc_rounding_mode(UChar *buf, s390_round_t rounding_mode)
6323     {
6324        UChar bits;
6325     
6326        /* Determine BFP rounding bits */
6327        switch (rounding_mode) {
6328        case S390_ROUND_NEAREST_EVEN: bits = 0; break;
6329        case S390_ROUND_ZERO:         bits = 1; break;
6330        case S390_ROUND_POSINF:       bits = 2; break;
6331        case S390_ROUND_NEGINF:       bits = 3; break;
6332        default: vpanic("invalid rounding mode\n");
6333        }
6334     
6335        /* Copy FPC from guest state to R0 and OR in the new rounding mode */
6336        buf = s390_emit_L(buf, R0, 0, S390_REGNO_GUEST_STATE_POINTER,
6337                          OFFSET_s390x_fpc);   // r0 = guest_fpc
6338     
6339        buf = s390_emit_NILL(buf, R0, 0xFFFC); /* Clear out right-most 2 bits */
6340        buf = s390_emit_OILL(buf, R0, bits);   /* OR in the new rounding mode */
6341        buf = s390_emit_SFPC(buf, R0, 0);      /* Load FPC register from R0 */
6342     
6343        return buf;
6344     }
6345     
6346     
6347     static UChar *
6348     s390_insn_bfp_triop_emit(UChar *buf, const s390_insn *insn)
6349     {
6350        UInt r1 = hregNumber(insn->variant.bfp_triop.dst);
6351        UInt r2 = hregNumber(insn->variant.bfp_triop.op2);
6352        UInt r3 = hregNumber(insn->variant.bfp_triop.op3);
6353        s390_round_t rounding_mode = insn->variant.bfp_triop.rounding_mode;
6354     
6355        if (rounding_mode != S390_ROUND_NEAREST_EVEN) {
6356           buf = s390_set_fpc_rounding_mode(buf, rounding_mode);
6357        }
6358     
6359        switch (insn->size) {
6360        case 4:
6361           switch (insn->variant.bfp_triop.tag) {
6362           case S390_BFP_MADD:  buf = s390_emit_MAEBR(buf, r1, r3, r2); break;
6363           case S390_BFP_MSUB:  buf = s390_emit_MSEBR(buf, r1, r3, r2); break;
6364           default:  goto fail;
6365           }
6366           break;
6367     
6368        case 8:
6369           switch (insn->variant.bfp_triop.tag) {
6370           case S390_BFP_MADD:  buf = s390_emit_MADBR(buf, r1, r3, r2); break;
6371           case S390_BFP_MSUB:  buf = s390_emit_MSDBR(buf, r1, r3, r2); break;
6372           default:  goto fail;
6373           }
6374           break;
6375     
6376        default:  goto fail;
6377        }
6378     
6379        if (rounding_mode != S390_ROUND_NEAREST_EVEN) {
6380           /* Restore FPC register from guest state */
6381           buf = s390_emit_LFPC(buf, S390_REGNO_GUEST_STATE_POINTER,
6382                                OFFSET_s390x_fpc);   // fpc = guest_fpc
6383        }
6384        return buf;
6385     
6386      fail:
6387        vpanic("s390_insn_bfp_triop_emit");
6388     }
6389     
6390     
6391     static UChar *
6392     s390_insn_bfp_binop_emit(UChar *buf, const s390_insn *insn)
6393     {
6394        UInt r1 = hregNumber(insn->variant.bfp_binop.dst);
6395        UInt r2 = hregNumber(insn->variant.bfp_binop.op2);
6396        s390_round_t rounding_mode = insn->variant.bfp_binop.rounding_mode;
6397     
6398        if (rounding_mode != S390_ROUND_NEAREST_EVEN) {
6399           buf = s390_set_fpc_rounding_mode(buf, rounding_mode);
6400        }
6401     
6402        switch (insn->size) {
6403        case 4:
6404           switch (insn->variant.bfp_binop.tag) {
6405           case S390_BFP_ADD:     buf = s390_emit_AEBR(buf, r1, r2);  break;
6406           case S390_BFP_SUB:     buf = s390_emit_SEBR(buf, r1, r2);  break;
6407           case S390_BFP_MUL:     buf = s390_emit_MEEBR(buf, r1, r2); break;
6408           case S390_BFP_DIV:     buf = s390_emit_DEBR(buf, r1, r2);  break;
6409           default:  goto fail;
6410           }
6411           break;
6412     
6413        case 8:
6414           switch (insn->variant.bfp_binop.tag) {
6415           case S390_BFP_ADD:     buf = s390_emit_ADBR(buf, r1, r2); break;
6416           case S390_BFP_SUB:     buf = s390_emit_SDBR(buf, r1, r2); break;
6417           case S390_BFP_MUL:     buf = s390_emit_MDBR(buf, r1, r2); break;
6418           case S390_BFP_DIV:     buf = s390_emit_DDBR(buf, r1, r2); break;
6419           default:  goto fail;
6420           }
6421           break;
6422     
6423        default:  goto fail;
6424        }
6425     
6426        if (rounding_mode != S390_ROUND_NEAREST_EVEN) {
6427           /* Restore FPC register from guest state */
6428           buf = s390_emit_LFPC(buf, S390_REGNO_GUEST_STATE_POINTER,
6429                                OFFSET_s390x_fpc);
6430        }
6431        return buf;
6432     
6433      fail:
6434        vpanic("s390_insn_bfp_binop_emit");
6435     }

6437     
6438     static UChar *
6439     s390_insn_bfp_unop_emit(UChar *buf, const s390_insn *insn)
6440     {
6441        UInt  r1 = hregNumber(insn->variant.bfp_unop.dst);
6442        UInt  r2 = hregNumber(insn->variant.bfp_unop.op);
6443        s390_round_t rounding_mode = insn->variant.bfp_unop.rounding_mode;
6444        s390_round_t m3 = rounding_mode;
6445     
6446        /* The "convert to fixed" instructions have a field for the rounding
6447           mode and no FPC modification is necessary. So we handle them
6448           upfront. */
6449        switch (insn->variant.bfp_unop.tag) {
6450        case S390_BFP_F32_TO_I32:  return s390_emit_CFEBR(buf, m3, r1, r2);
6451        case S390_BFP_F64_TO_I32:  return s390_emit_CFDBR(buf, m3, r1, r2);
6452        case S390_BFP_F32_TO_I64:  return s390_emit_CGEBR(buf, m3, r1, r2);
6453        case S390_BFP_F64_TO_I64:  return s390_emit_CGDBR(buf, m3, r1, r2);
6454        default: break;
6455        }
6456     
6457        /* For all other insns if a special rounding mode is requested,
6458           we need to set the FPC first and restore it later. */
6459        if (rounding_mode != S390_ROUND_NEAREST_EVEN) {
6460           buf = s390_set_fpc_rounding_mode(buf, rounding_mode);
6461        }
6462     
6463        switch (insn->variant.bfp_unop.tag) {
6464        case S390_BFP_ABS:
6465           switch (insn->size) {
6466           case 4:   buf = s390_emit_LPEBR(buf, r1, r2); break;
6467           case 8:   buf = s390_emit_LPDBR(buf, r1, r2); break;
6468           case 16:  buf = s390_emit_LPXBR(buf, r1, r2); break;
6469           default:  goto fail;
6470           }
6471           break;
6472     
6473        case S390_BFP_NABS:
6474           switch (insn->size) {
6475           case 4:   buf = s390_emit_LNEBR(buf, r1, r2); break;
6476           case 8:   buf = s390_emit_LNDBR(buf, r1, r2); break;
6477           case 16:  buf = s390_emit_LNXBR(buf, r1, r2); break;
6478           default:  goto fail;
6479           }
6480           break;
6481     
6482        case S390_BFP_NEG:
6483           switch (insn->size) {
6484           case 4:   buf = s390_emit_LCEBR(buf, r1, r2); break;
6485           case 8:   buf = s390_emit_LCDBR(buf, r1, r2); break;
6486           case 16:  buf = s390_emit_LCXBR(buf, r1, r2); break;
6487           default:  goto fail;
6488           }
6489           break;
6490     
6491        case S390_BFP_SQRT:
6492           switch (insn->size) {
6493           case 4:   buf = s390_emit_SQEBR(buf, r1, r2); break;
6494           case 8:   buf = s390_emit_SQDBR(buf, r1, r2); break;
6495           case 16:  buf = s390_emit_SQXBR(buf, r1, r2); break;
6496           default:  goto fail;
6497           }
6498           break;
6499     
6500        case S390_BFP_I32_TO_F32:  buf = s390_emit_CEFBR(buf, r1, r2); break;
6501        case S390_BFP_I32_TO_F64:  buf = s390_emit_CDFBR(buf, r1, r2); break;
6502        case S390_BFP_I32_TO_F128: buf = s390_emit_CXFBR(buf, r1, r2); break;
6503        case S390_BFP_I64_TO_F32:  buf = s390_emit_CEGBR(buf, r1, r2); break;
6504        case S390_BFP_I64_TO_F64:  buf = s390_emit_CDGBR(buf, r1, r2); break;
6505        case S390_BFP_I64_TO_F128: buf = s390_emit_CXGBR(buf, r1, r2); break;
6506     
6507        case S390_BFP_F32_TO_F64:  buf = s390_emit_LDEBR(buf, r1, r2); break;
6508        case S390_BFP_F32_TO_F128: buf = s390_emit_LXEBR(buf, r1, r2); break;
6509        case S390_BFP_F64_TO_F32:  buf = s390_emit_LEDBR(buf, r1, r2); break;
6510        case S390_BFP_F64_TO_F128: buf = s390_emit_LXDBR(buf, r1, r2); break;
6511     
6512        default: goto fail;
6513        }
6514     
6515        if (rounding_mode != S390_ROUND_NEAREST_EVEN) {
6516           /* Restore FPC register from guest state */
6517           buf = s390_emit_LFPC(buf, S390_REGNO_GUEST_STATE_POINTER,
6518                                OFFSET_s390x_fpc);   // fpc = guest_fpc
6519        }
6520        return buf;
6521     
6522      fail:
6523        vpanic("s390_insn_bfp_unop_emit");
6524     }
6525     
6526     
6527     static UChar *
6528     s390_insn_bfp_compare_emit(UChar *buf, const s390_insn *insn)
6529     {
6530        UInt dst = hregNumber(insn->variant.bfp_compare.dst);
6531        UInt r1  = hregNumber(insn->variant.bfp_compare.op1);
6532        UInt r2  = hregNumber(insn->variant.bfp_compare.op2);
6533     
6534        switch (insn->size) {
6535        case 4:
6536           buf = s390_emit_CEBR(buf, r1, r2);
6537           break;
6538     
6539        case 8:
6540           buf = s390_emit_CDBR(buf, r1, r2);
6541           break;
6542     
6543        default:  goto fail;
6544        }
6545     
6546        return s390_emit_load_cc(buf, dst);  /* Load condition code into DST */
6547     
6548      fail:
6549        vpanic("s390_insn_bfp_compare_emit");
6550     }
6551     
6552     
6553     static UChar *
6554     s390_insn_bfp128_binop_emit(UChar *buf, const s390_insn *insn)
6555     {
6556        UInt r1_hi = hregNumber(insn->variant.bfp128_binop.dst_hi);
6557        UInt r1_lo = hregNumber(insn->variant.bfp128_binop.dst_lo);
6558        UInt r2_hi = hregNumber(insn->variant.bfp128_binop.op2_hi);
6559        UInt r2_lo = hregNumber(insn->variant.bfp128_binop.op2_lo);
6560        s390_round_t rounding_mode = insn->variant.bfp_binop.rounding_mode;
6561     
6562        /* Paranoia */
6563        vassert(insn->size == 16);
6564        vassert(r1_lo == r1_hi + 2);
6565        vassert(r2_lo == r2_hi + 2);
6566        vassert((r1_hi & 0x2) == 0);
6567        vassert((r2_hi & 0x2) == 0);
6568     
6569        if (rounding_mode != S390_ROUND_NEAREST_EVEN) {
6570           buf = s390_set_fpc_rounding_mode(buf, rounding_mode);
6571        }
6572     
6573        switch (insn->variant.bfp128_binop.tag) {
6574        case S390_BFP_ADD:     buf = s390_emit_AXBR(buf, r1_hi, r2_hi); break;
6575        case S390_BFP_SUB:     buf = s390_emit_SXBR(buf, r1_hi, r2_hi); break;
6576        case S390_BFP_MUL:     buf = s390_emit_MXBR(buf, r1_hi, r2_hi); break;
6577        case S390_BFP_DIV:     buf = s390_emit_DXBR(buf, r1_hi, r2_hi); break;
6578        default:  goto fail;
6579        }
6580     
6581        if (rounding_mode != S390_ROUND_NEAREST_EVEN) {
6582           /* Restore FPC register from guest state */
6583           buf = s390_emit_LFPC(buf, S390_REGNO_GUEST_STATE_POINTER,
6584                                OFFSET_s390x_fpc);   // fpc = guest_fpc
6585        }
6586        return buf;
6587     
6588      fail:
6589        vpanic("s390_insn_bfp128_binop_emit");
6590     }
6591     
6592     
6593     static UChar *
6594     s390_insn_bfp128_compare_emit(UChar *buf, const s390_insn *insn)
6595     {
6596        UInt dst   = hregNumber(insn->variant.bfp128_compare.dst);
6597        UInt r1_hi = hregNumber(insn->variant.bfp128_compare.op1_hi);
6598        UInt r1_lo = hregNumber(insn->variant.bfp128_compare.op1_lo);
6599        UInt r2_hi = hregNumber(insn->variant.bfp128_compare.op2_hi);
6600        UInt r2_lo = hregNumber(insn->variant.bfp128_compare.op2_lo);
6601     
6602        /* Paranoia */
6603        vassert(insn->size == 16);
6604        vassert(r1_lo == r1_hi + 2);
6605        vassert(r2_lo == r2_hi + 2);
6606        vassert((r1_hi & 0x2) == 0);
6607        vassert((r2_hi & 0x2) == 0);
6608     
6609        buf = s390_emit_CXBR(buf, r1_hi, r2_hi);
6610     
6611        /* Load condition code into DST */
6612        return s390_emit_load_cc(buf, dst);
6613     }
6614     
6615     
6616     static UChar *
6617     s390_insn_bfp128_unop_emit(UChar *buf, const s390_insn *insn)
6618     {
6619        UInt r1_hi = hregNumber(insn->variant.bfp128_unop.dst_hi);
6620        UInt r1_lo = hregNumber(insn->variant.bfp128_unop.dst_lo);
6621        UInt r2_hi = hregNumber(insn->variant.bfp128_unop.op_hi);
6622        UInt r2_lo = hregNumber(insn->variant.bfp128_unop.op_lo);
6623        s390_round_t rounding_mode = insn->variant.bfp_binop.rounding_mode;
6624     
6625        /* Paranoia */
6626        vassert(insn->size == 16);
6627        vassert(r1_lo == r1_hi + 2);
6628        vassert(r2_lo == r2_hi + 2);
6629        vassert((r1_hi & 0x2) == 0);
6630        vassert((r2_hi & 0x2) == 0);
6631     
6632        if (rounding_mode != S390_ROUND_NEAREST_EVEN) {
6633           buf = s390_set_fpc_rounding_mode(buf, rounding_mode);
6634        }
6635     
6636        switch (insn->variant.bfp128_unop.tag) {
6637        case S390_BFP_ABS:         buf = s390_emit_LPXBR(buf, r1_hi, r2_hi); break;
6638        case S390_BFP_NABS:        buf = s390_emit_LNXBR(buf, r1_hi, r2_hi); break;
6639        case S390_BFP_NEG:         buf = s390_emit_LCXBR(buf, r1_hi, r2_hi); break;
6640        case S390_BFP_SQRT:        buf = s390_emit_SQXBR(buf, r1_hi, r2_hi); break;
6641        case S390_BFP_F128_TO_F32: buf = s390_emit_LEXBR(buf, r1_hi, r2_hi); break;
6642        case S390_BFP_F128_TO_F64: buf = s390_emit_LDXBR(buf, r1_hi, r2_hi); break;
6643        default:  goto fail;
6644        }
6645     
6646        if (rounding_mode != S390_ROUND_NEAREST_EVEN) {
6647           /* Restore FPC register from guest state */
6648           buf = s390_emit_LFPC(buf, S390_REGNO_GUEST_STATE_POINTER,
6649                                OFFSET_s390x_fpc);   // fpc = guest_fpc
6650        }
6651        return buf;
6652     
6653      fail:
6654        vpanic("s390_insn_bfp128_unop_emit");
6655     }
6656     
6657     
6658     /* Conversion to 128-bit BFP does not require a rounding mode */
6659     static UChar *
6660     s390_insn_bfp128_convert_to_emit(UChar *buf, const s390_insn *insn)
6661     {
6662        UInt r1_hi = hregNumber(insn->variant.bfp128_unop.dst_hi);
6663        UInt r1_lo = hregNumber(insn->variant.bfp128_unop.dst_lo);
6664        UInt r2    = hregNumber(insn->variant.bfp128_unop.op_hi);
6665     
6666        /* Paranoia */
6667        vassert(insn->size == 16);
6668        vassert(r1_lo == r1_hi + 2);
6669        vassert((r1_hi & 0x2) == 0);
6670     
6671        switch (insn->variant.bfp128_unop.tag) {
6672        case S390_BFP_I32_TO_F128: buf = s390_emit_CXFBR(buf, r1_hi, r2); break;
6673        case S390_BFP_I64_TO_F128: buf = s390_emit_CXGBR(buf, r1_hi, r2); break;
6674        case S390_BFP_F32_TO_F128: buf = s390_emit_LXEBR(buf, r1_hi, r2); break;
6675        case S390_BFP_F64_TO_F128: buf = s390_emit_LXDBR(buf, r1_hi, r2); break;
6676        default:  goto fail;
6677        }
6678     
6679        return buf;
6680     
6681      fail:
6682        vpanic("s390_insn_bfp128_convert_to_emit");
6683     }
6684     
6685     
6686     static UChar *
6687     s390_insn_bfp128_convert_from_emit(UChar *buf, const s390_insn *insn)
6688     {
6689        UInt r1    = hregNumber(insn->variant.bfp128_unop.dst_hi);
6690        UInt r2_hi = hregNumber(insn->variant.bfp128_unop.op_hi);
6691        UInt r2_lo = hregNumber(insn->variant.bfp128_unop.op_lo);
6692        s390_round_t rounding_mode = insn->variant.bfp_binop.rounding_mode;
6693     
6694        /* Paranoia */
6695        vassert(insn->size != 16);
6696        vassert(r2_lo == r2_hi + 2);
6697        vassert((r2_hi & 0x2) == 0);
6698     
6699        /* The "convert to fixed" instructions have a field for the rounding
6700           mode and no FPC modification is necessary. So we handle them
6701           upfront. */
6702        switch (insn->variant.bfp_unop.tag) {
6703        case S390_BFP_F128_TO_I32: return s390_emit_CFXBR(buf, rounding_mode,
6704                                                          r1, r2_hi);  break;
6705        case S390_BFP_F128_TO_I64: return s390_emit_CGXBR(buf, rounding_mode,
6706                                                          r1, r2_hi);  break;
6707        default: break;
6708        }
6709     
6710        vpanic("s390_insn_bfp128_convert_from_emit");
6711     }
6712     
6713     
6714     Int
6715     emit_S390Instr(UChar *buf, Int nbuf, struct s390_insn *insn,
6716                    Bool mode64, void *dispatch)
6717     {
6718        UChar *end;
6719     
6720        switch (insn->tag) {
6721        case S390_INSN_LOAD:
6722           end = s390_insn_load_emit(buf, insn);
6723           break;
6724     
6725        case S390_INSN_STORE:
6726           end = s390_insn_store_emit(buf, insn);
6727           break;
6728     
6729        case S390_INSN_MOVE:
6730           end = s390_insn_move_emit(buf, insn);
6731           break;
6732     
6733        case S390_INSN_COND_MOVE:
6734           end = s390_insn_cond_move_emit(buf, insn);
6735           break;
6736     
6737        case S390_INSN_LOAD_IMMEDIATE:
6738           end = s390_insn_load_immediate_emit(buf, insn);
6739           break;
6740     
6741        case S390_INSN_ALU:
6742           end = s390_insn_alu_emit(buf, insn);
6743           break;
6744     
6745        case S390_INSN_MUL:
6746           end = s390_insn_mul_emit(buf, insn);
6747           break;
6748     
6749        case S390_INSN_DIV:
6750           end = s390_insn_div_emit(buf, insn);
6751           break;
6752     
6753        case S390_INSN_DIVS:
6754           end = s390_insn_divs_emit(buf, insn);
6755           break;
6756     
6757        case S390_INSN_CLZ:
6758           end = s390_insn_clz_emit(buf, insn);
6759           break;
6760     
6761        case S390_INSN_UNOP:
6762           end = s390_insn_unop_emit(buf, insn);
6763           break;
6764     
6765        case S390_INSN_TEST:
6766           end = s390_insn_test_emit(buf, insn);
6767           break;
6768     
6769        case S390_INSN_CC2BOOL:
6770           end = s390_insn_cc2bool_emit(buf, insn);
6771           break;
6772     
6773        case S390_INSN_CAS:
6774           end = s390_insn_cas_emit(buf, insn);
6775           break;
6776     
6777        case S390_INSN_COMPARE:
6778           end = s390_insn_compare_emit(buf, insn);
6779           break;
6780     
6781        case S390_INSN_BRANCH:
6782           end = s390_insn_branch_emit(buf, insn);
6783           break;
6784     
6785        case S390_INSN_HELPER_CALL:
6786           end = s390_insn_helper_call_emit(buf, insn);
6787           break;
6788     
6789        case S390_INSN_BFP_TRIOP:
6790           end = s390_insn_bfp_triop_emit(buf, insn);
6791           break;
6792     
6793        case S390_INSN_BFP_BINOP:
6794           end = s390_insn_bfp_binop_emit(buf, insn);
6795           break;
6796     
6797        case S390_INSN_BFP_UNOP:
6798           end = s390_insn_bfp_unop_emit(buf, insn);
6799           break;
6800     
6801        case S390_INSN_BFP_COMPARE:
6802           end = s390_insn_bfp_compare_emit(buf, insn);
6803           break;
6804     
6805        case S390_INSN_BFP128_BINOP:
6806           end = s390_insn_bfp128_binop_emit(buf, insn);
6807           break;
6808     
6809        case S390_INSN_BFP128_COMPARE:
6810           end = s390_insn_bfp128_compare_emit(buf, insn);
6811           break;
6812     
6813        case S390_INSN_BFP128_UNOP:
6814           end = s390_insn_bfp128_unop_emit(buf, insn);
6815           break;
6816     
6817        case S390_INSN_BFP128_CONVERT_TO:
6818           end = s390_insn_bfp128_convert_to_emit(buf, insn);
6819           break;
6820     
6821        case S390_INSN_BFP128_CONVERT_FROM:
6822           end = s390_insn_bfp128_convert_from_emit(buf, insn);
6823           break;
6824     
6825        default:
6826           vpanic("s390_insn_emit");
6827        }
6828     
6829        vassert(end - buf <= nbuf);
6830     
6831        return end - buf;
6832     }
